<H3>POWER STATION TOURS</H3>
<HR>

<P>
Excursions can be arranged for students in Year 6 and upwards
to one of four large coal-fired power stations - Bayswater in
the Hunter Valley, Eraring and Vales Point are on Lake Macquarie.
All are within easy driving distance of Newcastle. You can also
visit Wallerawang Power Station at Lithgow.
<P>
All it takes is a phone call.
<P>
Bayswater Power Station..: (065) 42 0669
<P>
Eraring Power Station....: (049) 73 0596
<P>
Vales Point Power Station: (043) 52 6111
<P>
Wallerawang Power Station: (063) 52 8611
<P>
Community Relations......: (008) 45 1241 
</BODY>

