or around the world.
<P></P>
<HR>
<P></P>

<HR>
<P></P>
<H2>
PowerNet and <A HREF="/scippy/sciphome.html">Scippy Network</A> - Nuts And Bolts 
</H2>
<P></P> 
Pacific Power operates a large telecommunications network, used on a 
day-to-day basis for the administration and control of electricity 
generation for New South Wales.  By making use of spare bandwidth/capacity, 
this telephone network provides a free backbone service for the delivery of
electronic resources to remote primary and secondary schools across
New South Wales.<P></P>

<IMG SRC  = "/shared/images/earth160.gif">
In addition to the <I>backbone</I> service mentioned above, a
comprehensive coverage is achieved by establishing regional  HUB
systems owned and operated by pro-active schools to provide local
dial-in services to their surrounding STD areas - a kind of
"co-operative, cellular" distribution system.<P></P>
<P></P>

Individual schools and education based organisations have the option
to set themselves up as a HUB system, allowing authorised students and
their families to access PowerNet outside school hours.<P></P> Not all
schools will want to operate as regional hubs, and a number of
membership categories have been designed to meet the needs of
particular school/teacher and remote education situations. <P></P>
<P></P>

If you'd like more detailed information, about this and other
environmentally friendly products, then please read the <A
HREF="/shared/docs/schpol2.html"> <U>School Membership
Information</U></A><P></P> <P></P>

In September 1995 the BBS network started to change over to Internet Standards.
Check out <A HREF="/scippy/sciphome.html"> the latest Scippy Network </A> information pages. <P>

<H4><EM>PowerNet is designed to run without any need for
administrative overhead at the school site!</EM></H4><P> <HR><P></P>
<P></P>
