<H3>VIDEOS (AVAILABLE FOR SCHOOL LIBRARIES ONLY)</H3>
<HR>

<H4>The Greenhouse Effect - Part 1 (18 minutes)</H4>

<P>
The phenomenon known as the Greenhouse Effect has been around
since the earth was formed.
<H2>Why is the Greenhouse Effect such a concern today?</H2>

<P>
The naturally occurring gases that make up the earth's atmosphere
are essential for life. Some also play a role in trapping the
heat radiated from the earth's surface and help to maintain the
temperature at a pleasant 15 degrees celsius.
<P>
This video programme helps you understand what the Greenhouse
Effect is and what causes it.
<P>
It tells the story of how mankind's increasing numbers, development
and industrialisation have affected the natural balance that existed.
<P>
Greenhouse: Some Options - Part 2 (22 minutes)
<P>
The Greenhouse Effect is a natural phenomenon.
<P>
But in the 20th century the population of the earth has expanded
dramatically.
<P>
Many scientists believe that development and industrialisation
have begun to effect the natural balance!
<P>
This video looks at what the effects of global warming might mean
for the human race and the environment in which we live.
<P>
More importantly, it looks at some of the actions we can take
to try and tackle the prblems.
<P>
The important thing to remember is that looking after the environment
is everyone's responsibility, adn we should all be aware of the
options that are open to us.
<P>
Understanding the costs, benefits and implications of reducing
Greenhouse emissions is the first step in dealing with the problem.
<P>
Only then can informed decisions be made. 
</BODY>

