<H3><A NAME="01">[01]</A> FRIDAY'S EDITORIALS BY ANDREW N. GUTHRIE (WASHINGTON)</H3>
<STRONG>DATE</STRONG>=12/20/96<BR>
<STRONG>TYPE</STRONG>=U-S EDITORIAL DIGEST<BR>
<STRONG>NUMBER</STRONG>=6-09940<BR>
<STRONG>TELEPHONE</STRONG>=619-3335<BR>
<STRONG>EDITOR</STRONG>=PHIL HAYNES<BR>
<STRONG>CONTENT</STRONG>=<BR>
<CENTER>// EDITORS, PLEASE NOTE: THIS IS PERISHABLE MATERIAL AND BECOMES
DATED AFTER 10 P-M  E-S-T  ON FRIDAY, DECEMBER 20TH //</CENTER>
<P><STRONG>INTRO</STRONG>:   TERRORISM IN PERU AND MORE PROBLEMS IN RUSSIA'S
         BREAKAWAY CHECHNYA REGION ARE AMONG THE MANY EDITORIAL
         TOPICS DISCUSSED IN TODAY'S U-S NEWSPAPERS. OTHER
         SUBJECTS GETTING A LOOK ARE: A NEW CONTENT RATINGS
         SCHEME FOR TELEVISION PROGRAMS; ISRAELI SETTLEMENT
         POLICY CHANGES; ANOTHER COUNTERSPY UNMASKED, AND
         TEXACO'S INSTITUTIONAL RE-BIRTH.  NOW, HERE WITH A QUOTE
         OR TWO IS __________________AND THE U-S EDITORIAL
         DIGEST.
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    TODAY'S WASHINGTON TIMES IS WATCHING DEVELOPMENTS AT THE
         JAPANESE AMBASSADOR'S RESIDENCE IN LIMA, PERU, TAKEN
         OVER BY TUPAC AMARU TERRORISTS, WHERE ABOUT 400
         DIPLOMATS AND OTHERS ARE BEING HELD HOSTAGE.  THE PAPER
         SAYS IN PART:
<P><STRONG>VOICE</STRONG>:   &quot;THE BIGGEST ITEM ON THE TERRORISTS' AGENDA IS THE
         RELEASE OF HUNDREDS OF THEIR COMRADES HELD IN PRISON.
         BUT ALONG WITH THAT, THEY ARE DEMANDING NOTHING LESS
         THAN A TOTAL CHANGE IN THE POLITICAL AND ECONOMIC MAKEUP
         OF PERU, ALONG WITH THE OUSTER OF MR. FUJIMORI... UNTIL
         RECENTLY MR. FUJIMORI WAS CLAIMING VICTORY OVER
         MARXIST-TERRORIST ORGANIZATIONS IN PERU.  UNFORTUNATELY,
         IT SEEMS, HE SPOKE TOO SOON.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    THE WASHINGTON POST TODAY DECRIES ACTS OF TERRORISM BOTH
         IN LIMA AND RUSSIA'S CHECHNYA REGION, WHERE SIX RED
         CROSS WORKERS WERE SHOT TO DEATH IN THEIR SLEEP INSIDE A
         RED CROSS HOSPITAL. SAYS THE POST:
<P><STRONG>VOICE</STRONG>:   &quot;IT'S A LONG WAY, AND NOT ONLY IN MILES, FROM THE
         PRIVATIONS AND DANGER OF A PRIMITIVE VILLAGE HOSPITAL IN
         CHECHNYA TO A GLITTERING RECEPTION AT THE JAPANESE
         EMBASSY IN LIMA, PERU.  BUT THE TWO LOCATIONS WERE SADLY
         UNITED THIS WEEK AS INNOCENT PEOPLE BECAME VICTIMS OF
         TERROR.  IT IS IN THE NATURE OF TERRORISM, OF COURSE, TO
         CHOOSE THE MOST BLAMELESS AND DEFENSELESS AS TARGETS...
         THE FURY UNLEASHED BY A WAR AS SAVAGE AS THAT WAGED BY
         THE RUSSIANS AGAINST CHECHNYA CANNOT BE EASILY RETHERED.
         THE MESSAGE OF THE TUPAC AMARU REBELS ... IN PERU MAY BE
         CLEARER.  THESE ARE RUTHLESS MARXIST REVOLUTIONARIES
         SEEKING TO REVIVE THEIR FADING MOVEMENT... THE EFFECT OF
         THEIR CRIME, NO MATTER HOW IT TURNS OUT, WILL BE TO
         DISCOURAGE FOREIGN INVESTMENT, THUS DEEPENING THE
         POVERTY AND INEQUALITY THAT FEED MOVEMENTS SUCH AS
         THEIR'S.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    AND ONE LAST WORD ON THE PERUVIAN SITUATION FROM THE
         PORTLAND [MAINE] PRESS HERALD:
<P><STRONG>VOICE</STRONG>:   &quot;THE TERRORISTS CLAIM TO SPEAK FOR THAT HALF OF PERU'S
         POPULATION THAT IS QUECHUA AND AYMARA INDIAN, BUT IT IS
         THE INDIANS, IN FACT, WHO SUFFER MOST FROM THE TERROR.
         THE GUERRILLA MOVEMENT BRINGS DISHONOR ON THE INDIAN
         LEADER FOR WHOM IT IS NAMED.  SLAUGHTERING MORE
         INNOCENTS WILL ONLY ADD TO THAT DISHONOR.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    A FAVORITE DOMESTIC TOPIC TODAY IS THE NEW TELEVISION
         RATINGS SYSTEM UNVEILED YESTERDAY TO HELP PARENTS GUARD
         THEIR CHILDREN AGAINST UNDUE SEX, VIOLENCE AND ROUGH
         LANGUAGE ON TELEVISION.  SAYS THE LOS ANGELES TIMES:
<P><STRONG>VOICE</STRONG>:   &quot;MODELED AFTER THE MOTION PICTURE RATINGS SYSTEM ...
         DEVISED IN 1968 TO PREVENT STATES FROM TAKING ADVANTAGE
         OF A SUPREME COURT RULING PERMITTING THEM TO ESSENTIALLY
         CENSOR MOVIES BASED ON LOCAL STANDARDS... [THE] PROPOSAL
         WOULD RATE SHOWS ON THE BASIS OF AGE LEVELS OF CHILD
         VIEWERS... WHILE THE NEW SYSTEM IS BETTER THAN WHAT
         EXISTS NOW  --  LARGELY NOTHING - - IT STILL FALLS SHORT
         OF MEETING THE LEGITIMATE CONCERNS OF MANY PARENTS.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    USA TODAY IS EVEN LESS ENTHUSIASTIC ABOUT THE PROPOSED
         TELEVISION RATING SYSTEM.
<P><STRONG>VOICE</STRONG>:   &quot;AN INDUSTRY COMMITTEE THAT 'VOLUNTEERED' TO DESIGN AN
         ELECTRONICS-COMPATIBLE RATING SYSTEM FOR PARENTS
         CONCERNED ABOUT TV VIOLENCE, LANGUAGE AND SEX EMERGED
         THURSDAY WITH A STONE-AGE SOLUTION: CLONE THE
         INADEQUATE, 28-YEAR-OLD MOVIE RATINGS... BUT A SURVEY
         ... FOUND 80 PERCENT OF PARENTS WANT MORE DETAILED
         GUIDANCE... AN INDUSTRY THAT TREATS ITS AUDIENCE'S
         WISHES WITH SUCH CAVALIER DISREGARD SHOULD NOT WONDER
         WHY ITS VIEWERSHIP CONTINUES TO DECLINE.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    TURNING BACK  TO OVERSEAS MATTERS, TODAY'S ORLANDO
         SENTINEL IS CONCERNED ABOUT THE ISRAELI GOVERNMENT'S
         PLANS TO STRENGTHEN JEWISH SETTLEMENTS IN THE OCCUPIED
         WEST BANK, NOTING:
<P><STRONG>VOICE</STRONG>:   &quot;IT DOESN'T TAKE MUCH THOUGHT TO CONCLUDE THAT THE
         REVIVAL OF TAX BREAKS AND SUBSIDIES TO ENCOURAGE
         DEVELOPMENT OF ... [JEWISH] SETTLEMENTS ... IS FURTHER
         EVIDENCE OF A COUNTERPRODUCTIVE TREND.  THAT'S NOT
         ACCEPTABLE... WHETHER A PARTY DISRUPTING PEACE EFFORTS
         IS HISTORICALLY A FRIEND OR A FOE, THE UNITED STATES'
         VOICE SHOULD BE RAISED IN PROTEST.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    THE ARREST OF A TRUSTED, VETERAN F-B-I AGENTS AS AN
         ALLEGED RUSSIAN COUNTERSPY, THE THIRD SUCH ESPIONAGE
         CASE IN THE PAST FEW YEARS, HAS PROVOKED A WAVE OF
         EDITORIAL COMMENT.  SAYS THE NEW YORK TIMES:
<P><STRONG>VOICE</STRONG>:   &quot;IT WOULD BE UNREALISTIC AND NAIVE TO EXPECT THE UNITED
         STATES AND RUSSIA TO CEASE ALL SPYING ON EACH OTHER ...
         [BUT] AT A TIME WHEN THE UNITED STATES IS ASSISTING
         RUSSIA WITH THE DISMANTLING OF ITS NUCLEAR WEAPONS,
         BUYING HIGHLY ENRICHED URANIUM FROM RUSSIAN WARHEADS AND
         SUPPORTING INTERNATIONAL FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE TO MOSCOW,
         IT IS BAFFLING THAT THE C-I-A AND ITS RUSSIAN
         COUNTERPART ARE STILL TRYING TO OUTFOX [OUTMANEUVER] ONE
         ANOTHER AS IF THE COLD WAR HAD NOT ENDED.  THE GAME
         ITSELF SEEMS MORE IMPORTANT TO ITS PRACTITIONERS THAN
         THE REASONS FOR IT.&quot;
<P><CENTER><STRONG>[OPT]</STRONG></CENTER>
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    THE WASHINGTON POST, IN ITS EDITORIAL, TAKES A SLIGHTLY
         DIFFERENT TONE UNDER THIS HEADLINE: &quot;MORE TROUBLE AT THE
         F-B-I.&quot;
<P><STRONG>VOICE</STRONG>:   &quot;THESE HAVE NOT BEEN GOOD YEARS FOR THE F-B-I.  THE
         MISHANDLING OF HOSTAGE SITUATIONS HAS EARNED JUSTIFIABLE
         CRITICISM, THOUGH CHANGED RULES OF ENGAGEMENT HAVE
         IMPROVED PERFORMANCE.  HIGH OFFICIALS HAVE BEEN CHARGED
         WITH HIDING THE TRUTH ABOUT RUBY RIDGE [A POORLY HANDLED
         HOSTAGE SITUATION IN RURAL IDAHO IN WHICH FEDERAL
         AGENTS, A FUGITIVE'S YOUNG SON AND WIFE WERE ALL SHOT
         AND KILLED] AND FORCED TO RESIGN OR RETIRE.  THERE ARE
         SERIOUS QUESTIONS -- YET UNANSWERED --  ABOUT THE
         LEAKING OF CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION FROM THE F-B-I FILES
         TO WHITE HOUSE OPERATIVES ... [AND].  NOW A FAIRLY
         SENIOR AGENT IS CHARGED WITH SPYING FOR A LONG PERIOD.&quot;
<P><CENTER><STRONG>[END OPT]</STRONG></CENTER>
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    THE HUGE AMERICAN OIL COMPANY TEXACO IS WINNING PRAISE
         FROM TODAY'S PHILADELPHIA INQUIRER FOR ITS HANDLING OF
         SERIOUS ALLEGATIONS OF DISCRIMINATION AGAINST BLACKS AND
         WOMEN.
<P><STRONG>VOICE</STRONG>:   &quot;TEXACO, WHICH LATELY HAS BEEN PAYING FOR ITS SINS,
         EVENTUALLY OUGHT TO PROFIT FROM THE BOLD WAY IN WHICH
         IT'S REMEDYING THEM.  ITS NEW BLUEPRINT FOR OVERCOMING
         ENTRENCHED BIAS AGAINST MINORITIES AND WOMEN CAN UNTAP
         HUMAN POTENTIAL INSIDE TEXACO.  THE COMPANY ... NOW
         SOUNDS DETERMINED TO BECOME A NATIONAL MODEL FOR EQUAL
         OPPORTUNITY.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    AND LASTLY, THE WASHINGTON POST, IS CRITICAL OF MEXICO'S
         DOMINANT POLITICAL PARTY, THE P-R-I FOR STILL FAILING TO
         COME TO TERMS WITH CORRUPTION.
<P><STRONG>VOICE</STRONG>:   &quot;MEXICO IS NOT DOING VERY WELL ... FOR IT, POLITICAL
         REFORM OPENS A WAY FOR THE EXPRESSION OF THE EXISTING
         MASSIVE SOCIAL AND ECONOMIC DISCONTENT.  DEMOCRACY IN
         MEXICO, NONETHELESS, IS A VALUE THAT CANNOT BE DENIED.
         IT IS COMING, AND MEXICAN POLITICIANS WHO REACH FOR THE
         FUTURE MUST EITHER EMBRACE IT OR WASTE THEIR
         GOVERNMENT'S LEGITIMACY AND DEEPEN THEIR COUNTRY'S
         PAIN.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    WITH THAT, WE CONCLUDE THIS BRIEF SAMPLING OF EDITORIALS
         FROM TODAY'S U-S PRESS.
<BR><STRONG>NEB/ANG/PCH</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>20-Dec-96 11:20 AM EST (1620 UTC)</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>NNNN</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>Source</STRONG>: Voice of America
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="02">[02]</A> EURO STOCKS/THU (S) BY JACK HUIZENGA (LONDON)</H3>
<STRONG>DATE</STRONG>=12/19/96<BR>
<STRONG>TYPE</STRONG>=CORRESPONDENT REPORT<BR>
<STRONG>NUMBER</STRONG>=2-207719<BR>
<STRONG>CONTENT</STRONG>=_<BR>
<STRONG>VOICED AT</STRONG>:
<P><STRONG>INTRO</STRONG>:  SHARE PRICES WERE MIXED THURSDAY ON WEST EUROPEAN
EXCHANGES.  V-O-A'S JACK HUIZENGA HAS THE CLOSING MARKET REPORT
FROM LONDON.
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:  STOCK PRICES WERE UP IN BOTH PARIS AND LONDON.   EXPERTS
SAY INVESTORS WERE ENCOURAGED BY BETTER-THAN-EXPECTED TRADE
FIGURES FROM THE UNITED STATES.
IN PARIS, PRICES ROSE SHARPLY, WITH THE CAC-40 INDEX CLOSING UP
ALMOST 30 POINTS, ABOUT ONE-AND-THREE-TENTHS PERCENT.   PRICES
ALSO WERE UP IN LONDON.  THE FOOTSIE-100 INDEX ROSE 33 POINTS,
MORE THAN EIGHT-TENTHS OF ONE PERCENT.
BUT, THE GERMAN MARKET -- WHICH CLOSED BEFORE THE U-S TRADE
REPORT WAS ISSUED -- WAS OFF.  THE DAX-30 INDEX CLOSED DOWN 13
POINTS, ABOUT ONE-HALF PERCENT, BUT THEN ROSE IN LATER
COMPUTERIZED TRADING.
<P>ON THE LONDON CURRENCY MARKET, THE VALUE OF THE U-S DOLLAR WAS UP
AGAINST THE JAPANESE YEN, THE GERMAN MARK, AND THE BRITISH POUND.
<BR><STRONG>NEB/JWH/KL</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>19-Dec-96 1:21 PM EST (1821 UTC)</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>NNNN</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>Source</STRONG>: Voice of America
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="03">[03]</A> EURO STOCKS/FRI (S) BY JACK HUIZENGA (LONDON)</H3>
<STRONG>DATE</STRONG>=12/20/96<BR>
<STRONG>TYPE</STRONG>=CORRESPONDENT REPORT<BR>
<STRONG>NUMBER</STRONG>=2-207762<BR>
<STRONG>CONTENT</STRONG>=_<BR>
<STRONG>VOICED AT</STRONG>:
<P><STRONG>INTRO</STRONG>:  SHARE PRICES ROSE SHARPLY FRIDAY ON WEST EUROPEAN
EXCHANGES.  V-O-A'S JACK HUIZENGA HAS THE CLOSING MARKET REPORT
FROM LONDON.
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:  STOCK PRICES WERE UP IN PARIS, FRANKFURT, AND LONDON.
EXPERTS SAY EUROPEAN INVESTORS WERE ENCOURAGED BY THE SO-CALLED
SANTA CLAUS RALLY ON WALL STREET.
<P>ON THE PARIS MARKET, THE CAC-40 INDEX CLOSED UP ALMOST 30 POINTS,
ABOUT ONE-AND-THREE-TENTHS PERCENT, AND WAS UP ALMOST
THREE-AND-FOURTH-TENTHS PERCENT FOR THE WEEK.
<P>PRICES ALSO ROSE SHARPLY IN FRANKFURT.  THE DAX-30 INDEX CLOSED
UP ALMOST 47 POINTS, ABOUT ONE-AND-SEVENTH-TENTHS PERCENT, AND
ROSE EVEN MORE IN LATER COMPUTERIZED TRADING
IN LONDON, THE FOOTSIE-100 INDEX ROSE TO RECORD LEVELS, BUT THEN
SETTLED BACK, ENDING UP MORE THAN 26 POINTS, ABOUT SIX-TENTHS OF
ONE PERCENT, MORE THAN TWO-AND-ONE-HALF PERCENT FOR THE WEEK.
<P>ON THE LONDON CURRENCY MARKET, THE VALUE OF THE U-S DOLLAR WAS UP
A LITTLE AGAINST THE JAPANESE YEN,.  BUT THE DOLLAR LOST VALUE
AGAINST THE GERMAN MARK THE BRITISH POUND, AND ALL OTHER MAJOR
EUROPEAN CURRENCIES.
<BR><STRONG>NEB/JWH/KL</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>20-Dec-96 1:37 PM EST (1837 UTC)</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>NNNN</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>Source</STRONG>: Voice of America
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="04">[04]</A> NATO / BOSNIA / ENLARGEMENT BY ANDRE DE NESNERA (LONDON)</H3>
<STRONG>DATE</STRONG>=12/20/96<BR>
<STRONG>TYPE</STRONG>=CLOSEUP<BR>
<STRONG>NUMBER</STRONG>=4-09524<BR>
<STRONG>TELEPHONE</STRONG>=619-0932 (EDITOR)<BR>
<STRONG>EDITOR</STRONG>=PHIL HAYNES<BR>
<STRONG>CONTENT</STRONG>= // VOICER AND ACTUALITIES AVAILABLE IN A AUDIO SERVICES<BR>
<CENTER>//</CENTER>
<P><STRONG>INTRO</STRONG>:   THE NORTH ATLANTIC TREATY ORGANIZATION -- OR NATO -- IS
         TRYING TO REDEFINE ITS ROLE IN A CHANGING WORLD
         ENVIRONMENT  NO  LONGER POLARIZED BY SUPER-POWER
         RIVALRY. IN THIS REPORT FROM LONDON, V-O-A'S ANDRE DE
         NESNERA LOOKS AT NATO'S UPCOMING CHALLENGES AS IT MOVES
         TO ENLARGE ITS MEMBERSHIP TO INCLUDE EAST AND CENTRAL
         EUROPEAN COUNTRIES FORMERLY PART OF THE SOVIET BLOC.
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    THE NORTH ATLANTIC TREATY ORGANIZATION -- OR NATO -- WAS
         CREATED SHORTLY AFTER THE SECOND WORLD WAR AS A WESTERN
         MILITARY ALLIANCE AGAINST THE SOVIET UNION. AT THAT TIME
         NATO'S ROLE WAS CLEARLY DEFINED -- PROVIDE ITS MEMBERS
         WITH DEFENSIVE CAPABILITIES IN THE EVENT OF A SOVIET
         ATTACK.
<P>BUT THE DISINTEGRATION OF THE SOVIET UNION COUPLED WITH
         THE DISSOLUTION OF ITS NATO EQUIVALENT -- THE WARSAW
         PACT -- HAS FORCED THE 16-MEMBER WESTERN ALLIANCE INTO
         WHAT DEFENSE EXPERTS CALL A &quot;RETHINK" -- IN OTHER WORDS
         A REDEFINITION OF ITS ROLE NOW THAT ITS ARCH-ENEMY  NO
         LONGER EXISTS.
<P>EUROPEAN DEFENSE EXPERTS SAY NATO HAS HAD A TOUGH TIME
         REINVENTING ITSELF AND SOON AFTER THE COLLAPSE OF
         COMMUNISM, IT SEEMED TO DRIFT. THEY SAY THE CATALYST HAS
         BEEN THE EXPERIENCE IN BOSNIA, SHOWING NATO CAN BE
         FLEXIBLE AND ADAPT TO PEACE-KEEPING OPERATIONS --
         SOMETHING THE UNITED NATIONS WAS UNABLE TO DO.
<P>NATO'S CHIEF SPOKESMAN, JAMIE SHEA, SAYS THE
         ORGANIZATION'S ROLE IN BOSNIA WAS MILITARILY A SUCCESS
         IN TERMS OF STOPPING THE WAR.
TAPE :   CUT # 1     -     SHEA
         &quot;WE HAVE MANAGED TO DO THAT: SEPARATING THE FORCES,
         HANDING OVER THE TERRITORY, CREATING THE ZONE OF
         SEPARATION, DEMOBILIZING THE FORCES, SO THAT TODAY THE
         PROSPECT OF WAR IS QUITE REMOTE. BUT OF COURSE,
         UNFORTUNATELY FOR US AND FOR THE INTERNATIONAL
         COMMUNITY, THERE IS MORE THAN CREATING PEACE THAN IN
         STOPPING A CONFLICT. THERE IS A WHOLE ELEMENT OF
         RECONSTRUCTION AND RECONCILIATION THAT HAS TO TAKE PLACE
         AND UNFORTUNATELY, AS YOU WELL KNOW, WE ARE FINDING OUT
         THAT GIVEN THE HATREDS AND BITTERNESS THAT REMAIN, THIS
         IS PROVING A VERY, VERY SLOW AND FRUSTRATING JOB,
         INDEED. AND THAT IS ONE OF THE REASONS WHY INSTEAD OF
         LEAVING NOW AS WE HAD ORIGINALLY PLANNED TO DO, NATO IS
         GOING TO STAY ON FOR A FURTHER 18 MONTHS.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    THE NEW NATO CONTINGENT WILL HAVE 30-THOUSAND TROOPS --
         HALF THE NUMBER CURRENTLY IN BOSNIA.
<P>IN ADDITION TO FACING THE MILITARY CHALLENGES IN THE
         FORMER YUGOSLAVIA, NATO IS MOVING POLITICALLY INTO
         UNCHARTERED WATERS. THE ALLIANCE PLANS TO EXPAND ITS
         MEMBERSHIP TO INCLUDE COUNTRIES IN CENTRAL AND EASTERN
         EUROPE -- COUNTRIES FORMERLY PART OF THE SOVIET BLOCK.
<P>A FIRST GROUP OF NATIONS IS EXPECTED TO BE INVITED TO
         JOIN NATO DURING THE ORGANIZATION'S SUMMIT NEXT JULY.
         DEFENSE EXPERTS BELIEVE THE GROUP WILL INCLUDE POLAND,
         HUNGARY AND THE CZECH REPUBLIC -- AND MAYBE EITHER
         SLOVAKIA OR SLOVENIA.
<P>NATO'S EXPANSION EASTWARDS IS STRONGLY OPPOSED BY THE
         RUSSIAN GOVERNMENT.  PRIME MINISTER VIKTOR CHERNOMYRDIN
         -- SPEAKING THROUGH AN INTERPRETER -- MADE THAT CLEAR
         DURING A RECENT SUMMIT OF EUROPEAN LEADERS IN LISBON,
         PORTUGAL.
<P><STRONG>TAPE</STRONG>:    CUT # 2     -     CHERNOMYRDIN
         &quot;WE HAVE CLEARLY STATED, AND WE STATE ONCE AGAIN, THAT
         WE ARE FIRMLY OPPOSED TO PLANS TO MOVE UP TO OUR
         TERRITORY THE NORTH ATLANTIC ALLIANCE AND ITS MILITARY
         INFRASTRUCTURE. IT IS SURELY OBVIOUS THAT THE EMERGENCE
         IN EUROPE OF NEW LINES OF DIVISION WOULD LEAD TO A
         WORSENING OF THE ENTIRE GEO-POLITICAL SITUATION OF THE
         WORLD.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    MANY WESTERN DEFENSE EXPERTS BELIEVE RUSSIA'S OPPOSITION
         TO NATO ENLARGEMENT IS IN PART DUE TO LINGERING COLD WAR
         PERCEPTIONS.  PAUL BEAVER, SENIOR DEFENSE ANALYST WITH
         THE BRITISH PUBLICATION &quot;JANE'S DEFENSE WEEKLY",
         EXPLAINS.
<P><STRONG>TAPE</STRONG>:    CUT # 3     -     BEAVER
         &quot;I AM AFRAID THAT MOST OF THE RUSSIAN MILITARY AND
         KREMLIN FIGURES HAVE  NOT  YET GOT OVER THE FACT THAT
         RUSSIA IS  NOT  THE SOVIET UNION. THEY STILL BELIEVE
         THAT THEY ARE A MIGHTY WORLD POWER.  YOU JUST HAVE TO
         LOOK AT THE COMPLETE DEBACLE OF THEIR OPERATION IN
         CHECHNYA TO UNDERSTAND THAT THE RUSSIAN MILITARY IS  NOT
         WHAT IT USED TO BE.  IT IS STILL IMPORTANT, WE SHOULD
         NOT  BY ANY MEANS DISCARD THEM -AND WE MUST ALSO GIVE
         THE RUSSIANS THE CREDIT AND I THINK WE MUST UNDERSTAND
         THEIR POSITION. BUT THE RUSSIANS FIRMLY BELIEVE THAT
         NATO IS AN OFFENSIVE ORGANIZATION.  IT IS  NOT. I THINK
         IT HAS DEMONSTRATED THAT OVER THE LAST 47 YEARS  -- IT
         IS DEFINITELY WITHOUT DOUBT A DEFENSIVE ORGANIZATION.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    MR. BEAVER SAYS RUSSIAN OFFICIALS ALSO SEE NATO
         ENLARGEMENT AS BRINGING ABOUT A NEW IRON CURTAIN IN
         EUROPE.
<P>FRANCOIS HEISBOURG -- NATO EXPERT WITH THE LONDON-BASED
         INTERNATIONAL INSTITUTE FOR STRATEGIC STUDIES -- SAYS
         RUSSIA'S OPPOSITION TO NATO ENLARGEMENT MAY BE PARTLY
         DUE TO PSYCHOLOGICAL REASONS.
<P><STRONG>TAPE</STRONG>:    CUT # 4     -     HEISBOURG
         &quot;PRACTICALLY THE WHOLE RUSSIAN BODY POLITIC CONSIDERS
         THIS AS A HUMILIATING SETBACK FOR RUSSIA.  SO WHAT I
         FEAR IS  NOT  THE SHORT-TERM CONSEQUENCES WHICH WILL BE
         VERY WEAK, BUT THE LONG-TERM CONSEQUENCES THAT THIS WILL
         NOURISH A 'VERSAILLES TREATY TYPE SYNDROME' IN RUSSIA
         WHICH WILL COME BACK AND HAUNT US IN FIVE, TEN OR 15
         YEARS TIME.  THAT IS MY CONCERN -- AND IT IS VERY
         DIFFICULT TO FIND ANY RUSSIAN OF POLITICAL SUBSTANCE WHO
         WILL SAY OTHERWISE.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    MANY DEFENSE ANALYSTS SAY NATO'S ENLARGEMENT IS
         INEVITABLE AND WILL COME ABOUT SOONER OR LATER WHETHER
         RUSSIA WANTS IT OR  NOT.  CHIEF NATO SPOKESMAN JAMIE
         SHEA SAYS NATO HAS  NO  CHOICE BUT TO EXPAND BECAUSE
         FORMER SOVIET BLOC COUNTRIES ARE DEMANDING TO JOIN.
<P><STRONG>TAPE</STRONG>:    CUT # 5     -     SHEA
         &quot;TODAY, THE RATIONALE FOR ENLARGING NATO IS  NOT BECAUSE
         WE WANT TO EXPAND, BUT BECAUSE THE COUNTRIES OF THE EAST
         WANT TO GO WEST -- THEY WANT TO JOIN US IN THE WEST. IT
         IS BEING DONE MORE FOR POLITICAL AND SOCIAL REASONS IN
         TERMS OF UNDERPINNING DEMOCRACY AND ECONOMIC REFORM AND
         A SENSE OF BELONGING RATHER THAN FOR STRATEGIC REASONS.
         THANK GOD: THAT IS THE SIGN OF THE NEW EUROPE WE ARE IN.
         SO AS A RESULT, UNLIKE IN THE PAST, ENLARGEMENT OF NATO
         DOES  NOT  HAVE TO BE ACCOMPANIED BY THE SAME MILITARY
         CONSEQUENCES OF DEPLOYING FORCES, BUILDING BARRACKS AND
         BASES, HAVING HUGE EXERCISES OR DEPLOYING NUCLEAR
         WEAPONS.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    IN AN EFFORT TO REASSURE THE RUSSIANS, NATO HAS OFFERED
         TO BEGIN DISCUSSIONS WITH MOSCOW ON A DOCUMENT SPELLING
         OUT A NEW SPECIAL RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN NATO AND RUSSIA.
         NATO MINISTERS HAVE ALSO PLEDGED  NOT  TO STATION ANY
         NUCLEAR WEAPONS ON THE TERRITORIES OF NEW MEMBER STATES.
<P>DEFENSE ANALYST PAUL BEAVER SAYS THAT PLEDGE IS PURELY
         SYMBOLIC BECAUSE NATO RELIES ESSENTIALLY ON
         SUBMARINE-BASED NUCLEAR MISSILES FOR ITS DEFENSE.
<P><STRONG>TAPE</STRONG>:    CUT # 6     -     BEAVER
         &quot;TACTICAL, GROUND-BASED NUCLEAR WEAPONS LIKE CRUISE
         MISSILES ARE OUT OF VOGUE ANYWAY - NOBODY HAS GOT THEM
         ANYMORE. NOW THERE ARE VERY FEW ARTILLERY SHELLS. THE
         RUSSIANS MAY HAVE HUNDREDS OF THEM, THOUSANDS OF THEM
         STORED AWAY -- NATO DOES  NOT. NATO HAS GONE PAST THAT.
         ANYWAY, IT DOES  NOT  NEED TO: IT HAS GOT TRIDENT
         SUBMARINES - THE BRITISH AND THE AMERICAN DETERRENT AND
         THE FRENCH AS WELL HAVE GOT POWERFUL SUBMARINES. THEY DO
         NOT  ACTUALLY NEED THIS STUFF ON THE LAND ANYMORE. SO
         THERE IS ABSOLUTELY  NO  POINT IN HAVING IT THERE.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    NEW MEMBERS WILL BE INVITED TO JOIN NATO NEXT JULY AND
         WILL OFFICIALLY BECOME PART OF THE WESTERN ALLIANCE IN
         APRIL 1999 MARKING NATO'S 50TH ANNIVERSARY.  WHILE
         AGREEING THAT NATO EXPANSION IS INEVITABLE, SOME DEFENSE
         ANALYSTS BELIEVE THE PACE IS TOO FAST.
<P>FRANCOIS HEISBOURG -- FROM LONDON'S INTERNATIONAL
         INSTITUTE FOR STRATEGIC STUDIES -- SAYS THE WEST MAY
         HAVE RAISED ENORMOUS EXPECTATIONS AMONG THOSE COUNTRIES
         WANTING TO JOIN.
<P><STRONG>TAPE</STRONG>:    CUT # 7     -     HEISBOURG
         &quot;IT WOULD BE A TREMENDOUS DISAPPOINTMENT TO POLAND,
         HUNGARY, THE CZECH REPUBLIC AND A FEW OTHERS IF THE WEST
         WERE ALL OF A SUDDEN TO SIGNAL A SLOWING DOWN IN THE
         PACE -- AND INDEED THAT WOULD BE A MAJOR DOWN SIDE IN
         TERMS OF RELATIONS WITH THE NEW DEMOCRACIES. THAT BEING
         SAID, IF PRESIDENT CLINTON, NOW THAT HE HAS THE
         ELECTIONS BEHIND HIM, DECIDED THAT AFTER ALL MAYBE 1999
         IS  NOT  A DATE CAST IN STONE, I AM QUITE CONVINCED THAT
         IN PARIS, IN LONDON AND EVEN IN BONN, THERE WILL BE A
         COLLECTIVE SIGH OF RELIEF AND THERE WILL BE  NO
         COMPLAINING BY THOSE GOVERNMENTS ABOUT THE SLOWING DOWN
         OF THE PACE.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    EXPERTS AGREE NATO FACES A DIFFICULT TASK AS MOMENTUM
         BUILDS TO MAKE ENLARGEMENT IRREVERSIBLE. THEY SAY NATO
         MUST CONVINCE NEW MEMBER STATES IT IS SERIOUS ABOUT
         DEFENDING THEM IF THE NEED ARISES WHILE AT THE SAME TIME
         REASSURE RUSSIA THAT ENLARGEMENT POSES  NO  THREAT TO
         MOSCOW'S INTERESTS. AS ONE EXPERT PUT IT: &quot;NATO IS FACED
         WITH A DELICATE BALANCING ACT.&quot; (SIGNED)
<BR><STRONG>NEB/ADEN/PCH</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>20-Dec-96 1:08 PM EST (1808 UTC)</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>NNNN</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>Source</STRONG>: Voice of America
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="05">[05]</A> O-S-C-E/SERBIA (L) BY DOUGLAS ROBERTS (BELGRADE)</H3>
<STRONG>DATE</STRONG>=12/20/96<BR>
<STRONG>TYPE</STRONG>=CORRESPONDENT REPORT<BR>
<STRONG>NUMBER</STRONG>=2-207750<BR>
<STRONG>CONTENT</STRONG>=_<BR>
<STRONG>VOICED AT</STRONG>:
<P><STRONG>INTRO</STRONG>: AMID CONTINUING ANTI-GOVERNMENT DEMONSTRATIONS IN SERBIA,
A DELEGATION FROM THE EUROPEAN SECURITY ORGANIZATION (EDS:
O-S-C-E) ARRIVES (ARRIVED) IN BELGRADE FRIDAY, TO INVESTIGATE
CHARGES OF FRAUD IN NOVEMBER'S MUNICIPAL ELECTIONS.  THE O-S-C-E
MISSION, LED BY FORMER SPANISH PRIME MINISTER FELIPE GONZALEZ,
WILL MEET WITH SERBIA'S PRESIDENT SLOBODAN MILOSEVIC AND
OPPOSITION LEADERS, SEEKING WAYS TO DEFUSE THE MONTH-OLD CRISIS.
VOA'S DOUGLAS ROBERTS IN BELGRADE REPORTS SERBIAN OFFICIALS
INDICATE THEY MIGHT AGREE TO A NEW ROUND OF VOTING, BUT THE
RESPONSE FROM OPPOSITION LEADERS IS NOT YET CLEAR.
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:   IT WAS PRESIDENT MILOSEVIC WHO INVITED THE O-S-C-E
MISSION  HERE, SAYING HE WANTS THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY TO
LEARN THE TRUTH ABOUT LAST MONTH'S MUNICIPAL ELECTIONS.  ON THAT
ONE POINT, AT LEAST, MR. MILOSEVIC AND THE OPPOSITION LEADERS
AGREE.
THE &quot;ZAJEDNO" COALITION OF OPPOSITION PARTIES SAYS IT WILL GIVE
THE O-S-C-E DOCUMENTARY EVIDENCE OF ITS ELECTION VICTORIES IN
MORE THAN A DOZEN OF SERBIA'S MAIN TOWNS AND CITIES -- INCLUDING
BELGRADE.
<P>THE GOVERNMENT ANNULLED THE RESULTS, CITING IRREGULARITIES,
TOUCHING OFF THE MASS DEMONSTRATIONS BY OPPOSITION SUPPORTERS AND
UNIVERSITY STUDENTS, NOW IN THEIR FIFTH WEEK.
<P>OPPOSITION SPOKESMAN MILAN BOZIC SAYS THERE WILL BE NO END TO THE
PROTESTS, NOR ANY DIALOGUE WITH THE GOVERNMENT UNTIL IT ACCEPTS
THE INITIAL ELECTION RESULTS.
<CENTER><H4>///BOZIC ACT//</H4></CENTER>
<P>SO OUR POSITION IS: GIVE US BACK OUR CITIES, AND THEN WE
         CAN DISCUSS AND ENTER INTO NEGOTIATIONS ABOUT THE
         ELECTORAL PROCESS, ABOUT THE MEDIA AND SO ON AND SO
         FORTH.
<CENTER><H4>///END ACT///</H4></CENTER>
<P>SERBIAN OFFICIALS CONTINUE TO DENY THE CHARGES OF ELECTORAL
FRAUD, AND THEY SAY THEY WILL GIVE THE O-S-C-E MISSION EVIDENCE
TO SUPPORT THEIR CASE.
<P>O-S-C-E OFFICIALS SAY THEY WILL EXAMINE ALL RELEVANT DOCUMENTS,
BUT THEY HAVE INDICATED THE MISSION WILL  NOT  TRY TO MAKE A
DEFINITIVE JUDGMENT ABOUT NOVEMBER'S VOTING.
<P>SOME EUROPEAN OFFICIALS HAVE SUGGESTED IT IS MORE LIKELY THAT THE
MISSION WILL RECOMMEND A NEW ROUND OF ELECTIONS, MONITORED BY THE
INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY.  AT A NEWS CONFERENCE HERE THURSDAY,
FOREIGN MINISTER MILAN MILUTINOVIC SAID BELGRADE WILL CONSIDER
ANY SUGGESTION, INCLUDING NEW  ELECTIONS.  BUT HE SAID THE
GOVERNMENT WILL  NOT  BE BOUND BY THE O-S-C-E RECOMMENDATIONS.
<P>OPPOSITION LEADERS HAVE  NOT  YET EXPLICITLY DEFINED THEIR
POSITION ON A POTENTIAL NEW ROUND OF VOTING.  BUT THEY HAVE SAID
THAT THE O-S-C-E'S RECOMMENDATIONS SHOULD BE CONSIDERED MANDATORY
FOR THE SERBIAN GOVERNMENT.
<P>AMID THE ONGOING CONFRONTATION, SERBIA'S STATE-CONTROLLED MEDIA
IS CONTINUING A VITRIOLIC CAMPAIGN AGAINST THE OPPOSITION.  IN A
COMMENTARY PUBLISHED HERE FRIDAY, THE SERBIAN PRESIDENT'S
INFLUENTIAL WIFE, MIRJANA MARKOVIC, CHARGED THAT THE OPPOSITION
IS FOMENTING CIVIL WAR, AND TRYING TO PROVOKE FOREIGN
INTERVENTION.
<P>THE COMMENTS HEIGHTENED SUSPICIONS AMONG SOME LOCAL ANALYSTS THAT
THE GOVERNMENT IS PREPARING TO CRACK DOWN ON THE PROTESTERS.
OVER THE PAST FEW DAYS, THE RULING SOCIALIST PARTY HAS BEGUN TO
ORGANIZE COUNTER DEMONSTRATIONS IN SUPPORT OF THE GOVERNMENT.
AND SOME OPPOSITION OFFICIALS SAY THEY FEAR THE AUTHORITIES MAY
ATTEMPT TO ORCHESTRATE CLASHES BETWEEN THE RIVAL GROUPS OF
PROTESTERS, TO JUSTIFY INTERVENTION BY THE SECURITY FORCES.
<P>SENIOR GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS SAY THE POLICE WILL  NOT  INTERVENE,
AS LONG AS THE DEMONSTRATIONS REMAIN PEACEFUL. (SIGNED)
<BR><STRONG>NEB/DBR/PCF/KL</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>20-Dec-96 8:45 AM EST (1345 UTC)</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>NNNN</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>Source</STRONG>: Voice of America
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="06">[06]</A> PERRY / BOSNIA WAR CRIMES (L) BY DAVID GOLLUST (PENTAGON)</H3>
<STRONG>DATE</STRONG>=12/19/96<BR>
<STRONG>TYPE</STRONG>=CORRESPONDENT REPORT<BR>
<STRONG>NUMBER</STRONG>=2-207725<BR>
<STRONG>CONTENT</STRONG>=_<BR>
<STRONG>VOICED AT</STRONG>:
<P><STRONG>INTRO</STRONG>:  U-S DEFENSE SECRETARY WILLIAM PERRY SAYS THE ARREST OF
INDICTED WAR CRIMES SUSPECTS IS CRITICAL TO HOPES FOR LONG-TERM
PEACE IN BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA.  THE UNITED STATES AND ITS NATO
PARTNERS ARE DISCUSSING FORMATION OF A SPECIAL POLICE FORCE TO
HUNT DOWN AND ARREST THEM.  V-O-A'S DAVID GOLLUST HAS DETAILS
FROM THE PENTAGON.
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:  THE ISSUE OF THE PROPOSED POLICE FORCE FIGURED HEAVILY IN
THE DISCUSSIONS AT THIS WEEK'S NATO DEFENSE MINISTERS MEETING IN
BRUSSELS. AND MR. PERRY SAYS THE DEFENSE CHIEFS BELIEVE IT IS
&quot;CRITICALLY IMPORTANT" TO LONG-TERM PEACE IN BOSNIA TO BRING THE
INDICTED WAR CRIMINALS TO JUSTICE.
<P>ONLY A HANDFUL OF THE MORE THAN 70 PEOPLE INDICTED FOR WAR CRIMES
DURING THE BOSNIAN WAR HAVE ACTUALLY BEEN HANDED OVER OR
SURRENDERED TO THE U-N WAR CRIMES TRIBUNAL IN THE HAGUE.
<P>IN A TALK WITH REPOPTERS HERE, MR. PERRY SAID NATO MINISTERS ALL
AGREE THIS IS UNACCEPTABLE AND THAT THEY WOULD -- AS HE PUT IT --
&quot;MORE THAN JUST URGE" THEIR RESPECTIVE GOVERNMENTS TO CREATE THE
SPECIAL POLICE FORCE.
<P>THE DEFENSE SECRETARY SAID THE ISSUE IS UNDER STUDY BY AN
INTER-AGENCY TEAM IN WASHINGTON, BUT DECLINED TO GIVE DETAILS ON
HOW THE POLICE FORCE MIGHT BE SET UP OR WHAT THE AMERICAN ROLE
MIGHT BE.
<P>AT THE WHITE HOUSE, SPOKESMAN MIKE MCCURRY SAID THE
ADMINISTRATION BELIEVES THERE SHOULD BE AN &quot;ENHANCED EFFORT" TO
FULFILL OBLIGATIONS TO THE WAR CRIMES TRIBUNAL. BUT HE SAID THE
APPREHENSION OF SUSPECTS SHOULD NOT BE A JOB FOR THE NEW NATO-LED
STABILIZATION FORCE IN BOSNIA, KNOWN AS S-FOR:
<CENTER><H4>/// MCCURRY ACTUALITY ///</H4></CENTER>
<P>THAT IS NOT A MISSION OBJECTIVE OF THE STABILIZATION
         FORCE THAT NOW, AS OF TODAY, TAKES OVER SOME OF THE WORK
         THAT'S GOING ON IN BOSNIA.  BUT THERE WILL BE ADDITIONAL
         DISCUSSIONS OF HOW TO MAKE MORE EFFECTIVE THE EFFORT TO
         BRING TO PROSECUTION THOSE RESPONSIBLE FOR WAR CRIMES.
<CENTER><H4>/// END ACT ///</H4></CENTER>
<P>U-S OFFICIALS HAVE SAID THE POLICE FORCE COULD BE A PART OF THE
WAR CRIMES TRIBUNAL AT THE HAGUE OR UNDER THE AUSPICES OF THE
EUROPEAN UNION OR THE ORGANIZATION FOR SECURITY AND COOPERATION
IN EUROPE.
<P>MR. PERRY SAID ANY POLICE OPERATION WOULD, BY NECESSITY, WORK
CLOSELY WITH S-FOR, WHICH WOULD HAVE TO DEAL WITH CIVIL UNREST
THAT MIGHT BE UNLEASHED BY EFFORTS TO HUNT DOWN THE WAR CRIMES
SUSPECTS.
<P>THE MOST PROMINENT OF THOSE INDICTED ARE FORMER BOSNIAN SERB
LEADER RADOVAN KARADZIC AND HIS FORMER MILITARY CHIEF, RATKO
MLADIC -- BOTH OF WHOM RETAIN BROAD PUBLIC SUPPORT AND MOVE ABOUT
FREELY IN THE SERB-CONTROLLED AREAS OF THE COUNTRY. (SIGNED)
<BR><STRONG>NEB/DAG/RRM</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>19-Dec-96 3:32 PM EST (2032 UTC)</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>NNNN</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>Source</STRONG>: Voice of America
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="07">[07]</A> THE ROMANIAN REVOLUTION IN RETROSPECT BY JUDITH LATHAM (WASHINGTON)</H3>
<STRONG>DATE</STRONG>=12/19/96<BR>
<STRONG>TYPE</STRONG>=CLOSEUP<BR>
<STRONG>NUMBER</STRONG>=4-09518<BR>
<STRONG>TELEPHONE</STRONG>=619-3464<BR>
<STRONG>EDITOR</STRONG>=PHIL HAYNES<BR>
<STRONG>CONTENT</STRONG>=  (INSERTS IN AUDIO SERVICES)<BR>
<P><STRONG>ANNCR</STRONG>:   SEVEN YEARS AGO AT CHRISTMAS, THE WORLD WATCHED ON
         TELEVISION AS THE INFAMOUS ROMANIAN DICTATOR NICOLAE
         CEAUCESCU AND HIS HATED WIFE ELENA WERE TOPPLED FROM
         POWER IN THE BLOODIEST REVOLUTION IN EASTERN EUROPE.
         LAST MONTH [11/17/96], ACCORDING TO MANY POLITICAL
         ANALYSTS, THE ROMANIAN REVOLUTION WAS COMPLETED WITH THE
         ELECTION OF PRO- DEMOCRACY CANDIDATE EMIL CONSTANTINESCU
         [EH-MEEL KON-STAN-TI-NES-KOO] AND THE ROUSING DEFEAT OF
         THE INCUMBENT FORMER COMMUNIST PRESIDENT ION ILIESCU
<CENTER><H4>[YON IL-LEE-ES-KOO].  VOA'S JUDITH LATHAM TALKED WITH</H4></CENTER>
         EAST EUROPEAN SPECIALIST DANIEL NELSON, WHO JUST
         RETURNED FROM ROMANIA, AND WITH EAST EUROPEAN ANALYST
         DAVID BINDER [BYN-DER] ABOUT THE 1989 REVOLUTION IN
         RETROSPECT.  ________ HAS A REPORT, AS ROMANIA
         CELEBRATES THE BEGINNING OF A NON-COMMUNIST ERA.
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    DANIEL NELSON, PROFESSOR OF INTERNATIONAL STUDIES AT OLD
         DOMINION UNIVERSITY IN VIRGINIA, SAYS THE POPULAR
         CHARACTERIZATION OF THE RECENT ELECTION OF ROMANIA'S
         FIRST NON-COMMUNIST PRESIDENT AS A COMPLETION OF THE
         REVOLUTION OF 1989 IS AN OVERSIMPLIFICATION.
TAPE A:  CUT ONE -- NELSON (1:14)
         &quot;THE EVENTS IN 1989 WERE VERY, VERY SIGNIFICANT IN
         ROMANIA AND SHOULDN'T BE CONSIDERED ONLY HALF OF THE
         CHANGE, GIVEN FROM WHENCE ROMANIA WAS COMING.  ONE OF
         THE PROBLEMS WITH THESE COMPARISONS IS THE FAILURE TO
         RECOGNIZE THAT ROMANIA, AND I MIGHT ADD BULGARIA AND
         ALBANIA, HAD HAD NONE OF THE PRIOR CHANGES THAT WERE
         EVIDENT IN MUCH OF THE REST OF EASTERN EUROPE.  THERE
         WAS OF COURSE SOLIDARITY IN POLAND.  AND THERE WERE
         WORKERS' UPRISINGS IN THE EASTERN PART OF GERMANY IN
         '53.  AND, OF COURSE, THE PRAGUE SPRING AND CHARTER 77
         [IN CZECHOSLOVAKIA] AND 'GOULASH COMMUNISM' AND JANOS
         KADAR FOR MANY YEARS IN HUNGARY.  SO TO COMPARE THEM
         WITH ROMANIA'S CHANGE IN 1989 WOULD BE VERY MISTAKEN.
         IT WOULD BE VERY UNFAIR TO SAY THAT 'ROMANIA ONLY
         CHANGED A LITTLE BIT -- HALFWAY -- IN 1989.'  FOR
         ROMANIA IT WAS AN EXTRAORDINARY CHANGE.  [OPT] EVEN IN
         POLAND, HUNGARY, AND THE CZECH REPUBLIC, THE PROCESSES
         OF TRANSFORMATION CAN'T BE SAID TO HAVE BEEN COMPLETED
         SUDDENLY IN 1989. THEY'RE STILL STRUGGLING WITH
         DEVELOPING POLITICAL PARTIES, COMPLETING PRIVATIZATION.
         ROMANIA MAY BE A LITTLE FURTHER BEHIND IN THIS, BUT
         THAT'S NOT BECAUSE THEY DIDN'T CHANGE A LOT IN 1989.
         IT'S RATHER THAT THEY HAD A MUCH STEEPER CLIMB AND A LOT
         FURTHER TO GO.&quot; [END OPT]
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    &quot;NEW YORK TIMES" REPORTER DAVID BINDER HAS BEEN
         TRAVELING TO ROMANIA SINCE 1963.  HE SAYS HE SEES THE
         EVENTS OF THE PAST SEVEN YEARS AS MORE EVOLUTIONARY THAN
         REVOLUTIONARY.
TAPE A:  CUT TWO -- BINDER (1:04)
         &quot;I WAS THERE JUST AFTER THE ROMANIANS MARCHED IN
         TIMISOARA AND THEN MARCHED IN BUCHAREST AND SOME OTHER
         CITIES AND WERE FIRED UPON BY MILITARY AND SECURITATE
         FORCES.  AND I'M A LITTLE UNCOMFORTABLE WITH PHRASES
         LIKE 'REVOLUTION,'  BUT IT CERTAINLY WAS AN UPRISING OF
         ALMOST NATIONWIDE PROPORTIONS. BUT THE IDEA THAT ONLY
         NOW IS THE REVOLUTION COMPLETED, I JUST FIND THAT
         SOMEWHAT AN OVERDRAMATIZED DESCRIPTION.  THE GOVERNMENT
         RUN BY ION ILIESCU FROM THE MOMENT CEAUCESCU LEFT THE
         CENTRAL COMMITTEE BUILDING IN DECEMBER 1989 WAS FROM THE
         BEGINNING A TRANSITION GOVERNMENT. THE ONLY QUESTION WAS
         HOW LONG THE TRANSITION WOULD LAST.  [OPT]  AND YOU HAVE
         TO KEEP IN MIND THAT AT THE TIME THAT CEAUCESCU FELL, OR
         WAS DRIVEN FROM POWER BY THE PEOPLE IN THE STREETS, THAT
         THE OTHER POLITICAL FORCES OF ROMANIA HAD BEEN ALMOST
         EXTINGUISHED, THAT THEY WERE PRACTICALLY NON-EXISTENT.
         SO THE COMMUNISTS TURNED SOCIALISTS TURNED, QUOTE,
         'DEMOCRATS,' UNQUOTE, WERE SORT OF THE NATURAL
         SUCCESSORS OF CEAUCESCU.&quot; [END OPT]
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    DAVID BINDER SAYS THAT WHAT HAPPENED IN ALL THE
         COUNTRIES OF CENTRAL AND EASTERN EUROPE WAS THAT THE
         COMMUNIST SYSTEM SIMPLY COLLAPSED, SOMETIMES WITH THE
         HELP OF A PUSH FROM THE STREETS.  HE SEES THE FALL OF
         CEAUCESCU AS ONE IMPORTANT EVENT, IN A CHAIN OF MAJOR
         EVENTS, IN 1989.
TAPE B:  CUT THREE -- BINDER (1:03)
         &quot;IT WAS A GREAT MOMENT IN ROMANIAN HISTORY, AND IT WAS A
         VERY CONFUSING MOMENT.  AND THERE HAVE BEEN CHARGES EVER
         SINCE THEN THAT THE PEOPLE WHO SUCCEEDED CEAUCESCU AND
         HIS PEOPLE AND THE SECURITATE OF THAT TIME STOLE THE
         SO-CALLED 'REVOLUTION' FROM THE PEOPLE WHO HAD BROUGHT
         ABOUT HIS DOWNFALL BY MARCHING AGAINST HIM IN THE
         STREETS.  I DON'T SEE IT IN THAT SIMPLISTIC A FASHION.
         I THINK THAT HISTORY TENDS TO MOVE, NOT IN SUDDEN FLOODS
         OF RIVERS, BUT RATHER IN A SLOW, STEADY FLOW, AND WHAT
         WE SAW HAPPENING IN DECEMBER 1989 AND THEREAFTER WAS A
         MOMENTARY QUICKENING OF THE FLOW OF THE RIVER OF
         ROMANIAN HISTORY.  [OPT]  IT WAS NOT AS CATACLYSMIC AN
         EVENT AS IT IS PORTRAYED SOMETIMES.  AND WHAT HAD
         HAPPENED IN POLAND AND HUNGARY AND THEN CZECHOSLOVAKIA
         AND NEIGHBORING BULGARIA HAD A SIGNIFICANT IMPACT ON THE
         ROMANIAN POPULACE. THEY WERE ABLE TO  SEE WHAT WAS GOING
         ON IN THOSE OTHER EAST EUROPEAN COMMUNIST COUNTRIES, AND
         THAT WAS AN INSPIRATION FOR THEM.&quot; [END OPT]
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    PROFESSOR DANIEL NELSON SAYS EMIL CONSTANTINESCU, THE
         NEW PRESIDENT OF ROMANIA AND FORMER RECTOR OF BUCHAREST
         UNIVERSITY, IS BOTH AN INTELLECTUAL AND A PRAGMATIC
         POLITICIAN.
TAPE A:  CUT FOUR -- NELSON (0:57)
         &quot;LLIESCU LOST A SUBSTANTIAL PORTION OF THE WORKER VOTE,
         AND HE LOST IT ON THE BASIS OF POLICIES, OR AT LEAST THE
         PERCEPTION OF POLICIES, THAT HE  HAD NOT HELPED THE
         WORKERS, SO THAT THEY VOTED ON THAT BASIS FOR A CHANGE.
         AND THIS WAS IN THAT SENSE NOT A PURELY INTELLECTUAL OR
         INTELLIGENSIA MOVEMENT -- BY NO MEANS. WHAT
         CONSTANTINESCU DID, BETWEEN 1990 AND NOW, WAS TO
         REPACKAGE HIMSELF, APPEAL TO A BROADER BASE OF VOTERS,
         AND SUCCESSFULLY SUGGEST THAT HE WOULD CARE FOR THEM AS
         ILIESCU HAD NOT.  SO THIS IS NOT ANYMORE AN INTELLECTUAL
         EVENT AND HAS A LOT OF MASS APPEAL. CONSTANTINESCU AND
         [ION] CIORBEA AND THE GOVERNMENT PROBABLY HAVE SIX
         MONTHS DURING WHICH TIME THERE WILL BE SOME POPULAR
         PATIENCE, BUT BY THIS TIME NEXT YEAR, I CAN GUARANTEE
         YOU THAT THE POPULATION AND PUNDITS IN ROMANIA WILL BE
         SAYING, 'WELL, WHAT HAVE YOU DONE?'  AND I HOPE FOR
         ROMANIA THERE HAVE BEEN RESULTS.  BUT, PRINCIPALLY IN
         THE ECONOMIC DIRECTION, IT'S GOING TO BE DIFFICULT.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    THE GOOD NEWS ABOUT WHAT IS TAKING PLACE IN ROMANIA HAS
         BEEN LARGELY ECLIPSED IN THE MEDIA BY WHAT'S HAPPENING
         ON THE STREETS OF BELGRADE AND BY COMPARISONS BETWEEN
         SERBIAN PRESIDENT SLOBODAN MILOSEVIC AND THE DEPOSED
         ROMANIAN DICTATOR CEAUCESCU.  PROFESSOR NELSON SAYS HE
         THINKS EAST EUROPEAN ANALYSTS SHOULD BE PAYING A LOT
         MORE ATTENTION TO WHAT'S GOING ON IN ROMANIA.
TAPE A:  CUT FIVE -- NELSON (0:44)
         &quot;THE REAL NEWS HERE IS THAT A COUNTRY THAT IS THE SECOND
         LARGEST IN THE BALTIC TO BOSPORUS CORRIDOR HAS VOTED
         OVERWHELMINGLY, HAS TURNED OUT, AND DECIDED FOR A CHANGE
         AND TRUSTED IN THE BALLOT BOX TO DO IT.  WHAT AN
         EXTRAORDINARY DEVELOPMENT!  HOW MAGNIFICENT,
         PARTICULARLY WHEN YOU COMPARE IT WITH THE BACKDROP,
         WHICH WAS A DESPICABLE DICTATORSHIP THAT LASTED A
         QUARTER OF A CENTURY, THAT OF CEAUCESCU, AND WAS A
         REGIME IN WHICH -- ALTHOUGH HE DIDN'T KILL A LOT OF
         PEOPLE -- MADE MOST OF THE PEOPLE WANT TO DIE.  IT WAS A
         TERRIBLE REGIME, AND OUT OF THAT HAS EMERGED
         NEVERTHELESS A PEOPLE THAT HOPE, THAT TRUST IN THE
         BALLOT BOX, AND SEE THE NEED FOR CHANGE AND MOVE IN A
         DIRECTION FAIRLY DECISIVELY.&quot;
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    THIS CHRISTMAS SEASON, DANIEL NELSON SAYS, IS A
         WONDERFULLY AUSPICIOUS TIME FOR THE ROMANIAN PEOPLE.
TAPE A:  CUT SIX -- NELSON (0:52)
         &quot;THIS IS AN INCREDIBLY HOPEFUL MOMENT FOR ROMANIA.  IT
         IS HOPEFUL BECAUSE THE VOTING TURNOUT WAS HIGH, THE
         VOTING DECISION WAS CLEAR CUT, THE OLD GOVERNMENT HAS
         LEFT IN GOOD ORDER, THE NEW GOVERNMENT IS ENTERING WITH
         SUBSTANTIAL TRUST AND ANTICIPATION ON THE PART OF THE
         POPULATION.   FURTHER, IT'S HOPEFUL BECAUSE FOR THE
         FIRST TIME THERE'S DISCUSSION, SERIOUS DISCUSSION, OF
         ROMANIA'S ENTRY INTO NATO.  [OPT] IT'S CERTAINLY NOT
         GUARANTEED, BUT THERE HAS BEEN PROGRESS IN THAT
         DIRECTION, AND OF COURSE HOPE BECAUSE OF THE AGREEMENT,
         THE ACCORD WITH HUNGARY [CONCERNING THE PROTESTION OF
         ETHNIC MINORITIES]. AT THE  SAME TIME, THERE ARE MANY
         CHALLENGES, AND THE CHALLENGES ARE PARTICULARLY
         EGREGIOUS IN THE ECONOMIC REALM, WHERE MANY SERIOUS
         EFFORTS ARE GOING TO HAVE TO BE MADE TO LOWER INFLATION,
         CONSTRAIN UNEMPLOYMENT, WHILE YET ACCELERATING
         PRIVATIZATION. AND THIS IS GOING TO BE A DIFFICULT YEAR
         OR TWO FOR THE NEW GOVERNMENT -- IN THAT RESPECT.&quot; [END
         OPT]
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:    PROFESSOR DANIEL NELSON SAYS HE WISHES THAT THE GOOD
         NEWS ABOUT ROMANIA'S DEMOCRATIC VICTORY WAS BETTER
         UNDERSTOOD AND MORE FULLY APPRECIATED IN THE UNITED
         STATES AND WESTERN EUROPE.
TAPE B:  CUT ONE -- MUSIC -- ROMANIAN CHRISTMAS CAROL (ESTABLISH,
         AND USE AT LIBERTY)
<BR><STRONG>NEB/JL/PCH</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>20-Dec-96 7:47 AM EST (1247 UTC)</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>NNNN</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>Source</STRONG>: Voice of America
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="08">[08]</A> TURKEY/IRAN (L-ONLY) BY ANBERIN ZAMAN (ANKARA)</H3>
<STRONG>DATE</STRONG>=12/20/96<BR>
<STRONG>TYPE</STRONG>=CORRESPONDENT REPORT<BR>
<STRONG>NUMBER</STRONG>=2-207756<BR>
<STRONG>CONTENT</STRONG>=_<BR>
<STRONG>VOICED AT</STRONG>:
<P><STRONG>INTRO</STRONG>: THE UNITED STATES HAS ISSUED NEW WARNINGS TO TURKEY
AGAINST HAVING CLOSER TIES WITH IRAN.  AS AMBERIN ZAMAN REPORTS
FROM ANKARA, THE WARNINGS COINCIDE WITH IRANIAN PRESIDENT HASHEMI
RAFSANJANI'S FOUR DAY OFFICIAL VISIT TO TURKEY.
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:  ON THE SECOND DAY OF HIS TOUR, PRESIDENT RAFSANJANI
ACCOMPANIED BY HIS WIFE, SON, TWO DAUGHTERS, AND OVER 200 IRANIAN
OFFICIALS AND BUSINESSMEN, INSPECTED TURKEY'S SOUTHEAST ANATOLIA
PROJECT GAP, A MULTI-BILLION IRRIGATION SCHEME COVERING THE
MAINLY KURDISH SOUTHEAST PROVINCES.
<P>MR. RAFSANJANI SAID IRANIAN NATURAL GAS WOULD PLAY A BIG ROLE IN
THE DEVELOPMENT OF THE REGION.  HE WAS REFERRING TO THE
23-BILLION DOLLAR NATURAL GAS DEAL SIGNED BETWEEN TURKEY AND IRAN
LAST AUGUST.
<P>THE NATURAL GAS DEAL, ALONG WITH TURKEY'S PLANS TO DOUBLE ITS
TRADE WITH IRAN, HAS ANGERED WASHINGTON.  U-S OFFICIALS CONFIRM
THAT THE IRANIAN PRESIDENT'S VISIT HAS RAISED CONCERN OVER THE
COURSE WHICH TURKEY -- A NATO MEMBER -- IS TAKING UNDER ITS
RECENTLY-ELECTED ISLAMIST PRIME MINISTER, NECMETTIN ERBAKAN.  ON
THURSDAY, U-S STATE DEPARTMENT SPOKESMAN NICHOLAS BURNS ONCE
AGAIN VOICED WASHINGTON'S OPPOSITION TO TURKEY'S TIES WITH IRAN,
SAYING IRAN HAD TO BE ISOLATED.
<P>PRIOR TO MR. RAFSANJANI'S VISIT, AN ANNOUNCEMENT BY PRIME
MINISTER ERBAKAN THAT HE WANTS TO DEVELOP MILITARY COOPERATION
WITH IRAN PROVOKED A STRONG BACKLASH FROM MEMBERS OF TURKEY'S
CONSERVATIVE &quot;TRUE PATH" PARTY, OR D-Y-P, WITH WHOM HIS ISLAMIST
&quot;WELFARE PARTY" HAS BEEN SHARING POWER OVER THE PAST FOUR MONTHS.
<P>DEFENSE MINISTER TURHAN TAYAN -- A MEMBER OF THE D-Y-P WING OF
THE ISLAMIST-LED COALITION -- SAID HE WOULD REFUSE TO SIGN ANY
MILITARY ACCORD WITH IRAN.  BUT ABDULLAH GUL, A SENIOR CABINET
MEMBER FROM THE WELFARE PARTY, SAID ON THURSDAY THAT TURKEY COULD
JOINTLY MANUFACTURE HELICOPTERS WITH IRAN.
<P>SOME ANALYSTS WARN THAT MR. ERBAKAN'S PLANS TO REDUCE CUSTOMS
TARIFFS WITH IRAN COULD ALSO JEOPARDIZE A FREE TRADE AGREEMENT
TURKEY SIGNED WITH THE EUROPEAN UNION LAST YEAR.  (SIGNED)
<BR><STRONG>NEB/AZ/PCF/KL</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>20-Dec-96 9:44 AM EST (1444 UTC)</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>NNNN</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>Source</STRONG>: Voice of America
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="09">[09]</A> U-N WEEK-IN-REVIEW BY ELAINE JOHANSON (UNITED NATIONS)</H3>
<STRONG>DATE</STRONG>=12/20/96<BR>
<STRONG>TYPE</STRONG>=BACKGROUND REPORT<BR>
<STRONG>NUMBER</STRONG>=5-35300<BR>
<STRONG>CONTENT</STRONG>=_<BR>
<STRONG>VOICED AT</STRONG>:
<P><STRONG>INTRO</STRONG>:  THE UNITED NATIONS HAS A NEW SECRETARY-GENERAL BEGINNING
JANUARY FIRST -- KOFI ANNAN OF GHANA;  MEANWHILE,  THE U-N
SECURITY COUNCIL CONDEMNS VIOLENCE AND HOSTAGE-TAKING IN
TAJISKISTAN AND PERU, AND CALLS FOR AN END TO NEW FIGHTING IN
SOMALIA.  VOA CORRESPONDENT ELAINE JOHANSON REVIEWS THE MAIN
DEVELOPMENTS OF THE PAST WEEK:
<P><STRONG>TEXT</STRONG>:  UNDERSECRETARY-GENERAL KOFI ANNAN -- THE HEAD OF THE U-N
PEACEKEEPING DEPARTMENT -- IS ABOUT TO MOVE UP TO THE
ORGANIZATION'S TOP DIPLOMATIC POST.  THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY THIS
PAST WEEK ENDORSED HIS NOMINATION AS THE SEVENTH U-N
SECRETARY-GENERAL.  HE IS THE FIRST U-N LEADER FROM SUB-SAHARAN
AFRICA.
<P>THE UNITED STATES FAVORED MR. ANNAN FOR THE U-N POST, AFTER IT
VETOED A SECOND TERM FOR OUT-GOING SECRETARY-GENERAL BOUTROS
BOUTROS-GHALI.  MR. ANNAN SAYS HE IS COUNTING ON THE CLINTON
WHITE HOUSE TO PERSUADE THE U-S CONGRESS TO PAY ITS HUGE DEBT TO
THE U-N OF OVER ONE BILLION DOLLARS:
<CENTER><H4>// ANNAN ACT //</H4></CENTER>
<P>IT IS  NOT  REALLY IN THE INTEREST OF THE U-S  NOT  TO
         PAY ITS CONTRIBUTION TO THE U-N.  IT OFFENDS FRIENDS AND
         FOES ALIKE.  THE U-S NEEDS THE U-N AND THE U-N NEEDS THE
         U-S, AND WE  CANNOT  OPERATE EFFECTIVELY AND EFFICIENTLY
         WITHOUT A SOUND FINANCIAL BASIS.
<CENTER><H4>// END ACT //</H4></CENTER>
<P>THE U-S CONGRESS STARTED WITHHOLDING U-N DUES ABOUT A DECADE AGO,
DEMANDING DEEP REFORMS.  A POWERFUL SENATE LEADER FROM CAPITOL
HILL (JESSE HELMS) CONGRATULATED MR. ANNAN ON HIS ELECTION AND
INVITED HIM TO WASHINGTON TO DISCUSS HIS PLANS FOR RE-STRUCTURING
THE ORGANIZATION.
<P>ISMAIL RAZALI OF MALAYSIA -- THE PRESIDENT OF THE GENERAL
ASSEMBLY -- TOOK A DIM VIEW OF A SECRETARY-GENERAL HAVING TO BEG
FOR MONEY THAT GOVERNMENTS ARE UNDER TREATY OBLIGATION TO PAY:
<CENTER><H4>// RAZALI ACT //</H4></CENTER>
<P>THE UNITED NATIONS SHOULD  NOT  BE DONOR DRIVEN.  AND
         ALTHOUGH FINANCE AND FINITE RESOURCES MAY BE FACTS OF
         LIFE, THE SECRETARY-GENERAL SHOULD  NOT  HAVE TO POSE AS
         A MENDICANT, PETITIONING GOVERNMENTS AND LEGISLATURES
         ALIKE.
<CENTER><H4>// END ACT //</H4></CENTER>
<P>THE NEW SECRETARY-GENERAL HAS SAID HE WOULD CONSIDER A TRIP TO
THE U-S CONGRESS.
<P>         -0-
<P>THE SECURITY COUNCIL SPENT THE LATTER PART OF THE WEEK EXPRESSING
CONCERN OVER AND CONDEMNING VIOLENCE IN VARIOUS PARTS OF THE
WORLD.  ON THE TAKING OF HOSTAGES IN TAJIKISTAN -- INCLUDING
SEVEN U-N MILITARY OBSERVERS -- COUNCIL PRESIDENT FRANCESCO FULCI
MADE A PUBLIC APPEAL:
<CENTER><H4>// FULCI ACT //</H4></CENTER>
<P>THE MEMBERS OF THE COUNCIL HAVE INSTRUCTED ME TO EXPRESS
         THEIR FIRM AND RESOLUTE CONDEMNATION OF THESE REPEATED,
         COWARDLY ACTS AND APPEAL FOR AN IMMEDIATE  AND
         UNCONDITIONAL RELEASE OF ALL THE HOSTAGES.
<CENTER><H4>// END ACT //</H4></CENTER>
<P>TAJIK GUERRILLAS THREATENED TO EXECUTE THE HOSTAGES UNLESS REBELS
RELEASED THE BROTHER OF AN OPPOSITION CHIEF WHO HAD JOINED FORCES
WITH THE GOVERNMENT.  THE HOSTAGE DILEMMA DEVELOPED AS TALKS WERE
UNDER WAY IN MOSCOW TO TRY TO END THE FOUR-YEAR OLD CIVIL WAR.
<P>ON THE SEIZURE OF HUNDREDS OF HOSTAGES AT THE RESIDENCE OF
JAPAN'S AMBASSADOR TO PERU -- THE COUNCIL PRESIDENT DESCRIBED THE
ASSUALT BY PERUVIAN GUERRILLAS AS A TERRORIST ACTION:
<CENTER><H4>// FULCI ACT //</H4></CENTER>
<P>THIS INTOLERABLE ACT CONSTITUTES ALSO AN ASSUALT AGAINST
         THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY AS A WHOLE.  THE COUNCIL HAS
         ALWAYS CONDEMNED TERRORIST ACTS WHATEVER THE
         CIRCUMSTANCES IN THE MOST UNEQUIVOCAL TERMS.
<CENTER><H4>// END ACT //</H4></CENTER>
<P>AND FINALLY, ON THE RESUMPTION OF FIGHTING IN SOMALIA -- THE
SECURITY COUNCIL ISSUED A FORMAL STATEMENT CALLING ON THE
FACTIONS TO REINSTATE A CEASE-FIRE.  DIPLOMATS WONDERED WHETHER
THE COMBATANTS WOULD EVEN RECEIVE THE MESSAGE, AND IF THEY DO --
WHETHER THE U-N HAS ANY REAL INFLUENCE IN THE COUNTRY.
<P>U-N TROOPS WERE FORCED TO LEAVE SOMALIA IN 1994 WHEN THEIR
PEACEKEEPING MISSION WENT AWRY AND THEY WERE DRAWN INTO THE
CONFLICT.  (SIGNED)
<BR><STRONG>UN/EJ/CF</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>20-Dec-96 3:52 PM EST (2052 UTC)</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>NNNN</STRONG>
<BR><STRONG>Source</STRONG>: Voice of America
