<H3><A NAME="01">[01]</A> MEETING OF PRESIDENT BERISHA WITH DP PARLIAMENTARY GROUP</H3>
TIRANA, DEC 20 (ATA) - Today the President of Albania Sali Berisha had a
working meeting with the Democratic Party parliamentary group.
<P>President Berisha stressed in the meeting the fact that the
government and the parliament have worked and are working with a special
commitment to implement the program of the Democratic Party.
<P>President Berisha appreciated the parliament for its work in the
adoption of new laws. The law under way for the electronic media and
creation of space for private mediae is a great achievement in the field of
information in Albania but also for the Albanian democracy.
<P>President Berisha stressed that although the law on justice is
considered as very good, a group of experts, among the best, in cooperation
with the Council of Europe, is preparing a better law which will be soon
sent to the parliament for approval.
<P>But, said Berisha, 1996 was the year of the wisest decisions of the
Albanians but it unfortunately has been accompanied with an increase of the
budgetary deficit. This has been because of an increase of expenses but a
result of non-realisation of the revenues because of the lack of responsibility
and the manifestations of corruption in the institutions which are directly
responsible for their realisation.
<P>&quot;I fully support and consider in full terms with the DP program the
lawmaking initiative of a group of deputies to present in the parliament a
package of provisions for the fight against crime and corruption.
<P>The aim of this package, said Berisha, is to give the deserved
response to the drug traffickers and those involved in prostitution, to
killers and those who abuse with children, fiscal evasion which threatens
to block the reforms and kills competition and the free market spirit, as
well as a number of other crimes such as illegal possession of arms,
smuggling, etc.
<P>&quot;The program of the Democratic Party and its commitments before the
Albanian electorate express clearly our solemn commitment to guarantee the
life, activity and property of the individual.
<P>&quot;I think that with this package of laws a very important step forward
is made in the realisation of this program,&quot; said Berisha. xh/E
<P><H5>Albanian Telegraphic Agency</H5>
<H3><A NAME="02">[02]</A> MEMBERS OF COMMISSION ON RENTING ACTIVITY OF FIRMS NOT YET DEFINED</H3>
TIRANA, DEC 21 (ATA) By Agim Baci: The parliamentary commission on
economy, budget, finance and privatization examined Friday the names
proposed by the commission to secure the transparency in the activity of
lending, which will pass for approval to a plenary session.
<P>&quot;We will soon inform you of the names which will make up this
commission&quot;, declared the chairman of the DP parliamentary commission, Ali
Spahia.
<P>The commission of economy discussed on the same day the draft-law &quot;On
the new customs evaluation&quot;, which passed for approval to the parliament,
in a plenary session.
<P>This draft-law helps Albania to be accepted as a full right member of
the World Trade Organization, because she has so far only the status of the
observer.
<P>&quot;Albania, which wants to become member of the WTO, is obliged and at
the same time interested in these methods of evaluation for the imported
goods, so that they are the same with those used by other member countries,
&quot; said Dhrima. /jz/mt/E
<P><H5>Albanian Telegraphic Agency</H5>
<H3><A NAME="03">[03]</A> LUSHNJA SPORT-CLUB SIGNS CONTRACT WITH ARGENTINIAN KEMPES</H3>
TIRANA, DEC 20 (ATA) - By Atlant Frasheri: The President of the Lushnja
Sport-Club Pellumb Xhaferri and the footballer of Argentine Mario Kempes
will sign Saturday a contract for the coming two years. Kempes will be paid
a total of 350 thousand dollars a year.
<P>&quot;I love football and I think that Kempes will make a great contribution
to this sport,&quot; said Xhaferri.
<P>&quot;I like to work in Albania,&quot; said Kempes, who is supposed to start on
January 3, 1997.
<P>The Lushnja Sport-Club has made another contract with a Nigerian
football player, who will start to play in the Lushnja football team in
January 1997. eva/xh/k
<P><H5>Albanian Telegraphic Agency</H5>
<H3><A NAME="04">[04]</A> CONTEST IN THE ALBANIAN LIGHT SONG FESTIVAL FOR 1996 CONTINUES</H3>
TIRANA, DEC 20 (ATA) - By Flora Nikolla: The 35th Song Festival which
started Thursday in the Palace of Congresses in Tirana brought on the stage
not only the best songs of Albanian light music within a year but it also
paid homage to Albanian song in the past festivals.
<P>Thirty two songs selected among 102 songs presented for the contest,
were interpreted in the festival. The prologue-festival shown during the
first two nights of the festival brought before two thousand spectators and
thousands of TV viewers the emotions of the festivals on radio-television
in the past years.
<P>A collage of Albanian folk songs brought before Albanian music fans
an original pop-folk.
<P>The contest was presented by the composer and singer Ardit Gjebrea,
who in the past festival won the first prize, the Miss-Photography of 1991,
presently student in Fine Arts in Athens, Valbona Coba.
<P>Four juries established in the cities of Korca, Shkodra, Gjirokastra,
Struge and one in Bari of Italy (Tele Norba) during the first two nights of
this Festival, through a direct line, reminded the participants that they
were together in the Festival and &quot;against them.&quot;
<P>Besides, there was another jury, that of the youths, based on the
telephone calls for the best song, which was directed by Rudina Magjistari.
kei/xh/k
<P><H5>Albanian Telegraphic Agency</H5>
<H3><A NAME="05">[05]</A> PRESS REVIEW</H3>
TIRANA, DEC 21 (ATA) Rilindja Demokratike highlights the yesterday meeting
of President Berisha with the DP parliamentary group under the title &quot;Blows
to crime and corruption&quot;. &quot;A group of deputies from the Democratic Party
presented Friday to the DP parliamentary group a package of laws, aiming at
neutralizing crime and corruption&quot;, reports the paper among others. &quot;Ulqini
requests again the postponement of the meeting of Tirana Leading Committee&quot;,
reports the paper regarding the yesterday debate, considered as a marathon
of the Tirana socialists.
<P>With regard to this meeting, Zeri i Popullit carries the article
&quot;Everything to the strengthening of the party&quot;. &quot;It is necessary to get
free from the complexes of the past and to evaluate the free debate as a
mean for the emancipation of the party&quot;, the paper cites the SP Secretary
General, Rexhep Mejdani&quot;. &quot;The parliament applies DP program&quot;, reports the
paper under the headline &quot;Through the labyrinths of Democratic Party&quot;.
<P>&quot;The State Control sues Tirana municipality&quot;, reports Republika paper.
&quot;VEFA, this Albanian giant&quot;, reports the paper regarding the ceremony held
Friday in Tirana on the occasion of the 5th anniversary of its foundation&quot;.
<P>Under the headline &quot;Democrats ready for the battle of the clean hands&quot;,
Albania carries the article &quot;Corruption under manacles!&quot;. &quot;Socialists
separate in a draw&quot;, reports the paper regarding the yesterday meeting of
Tirana SP, which was still postponed.
<P>Rilindja paper highlights the news conference of Kosova Democratic
League under the title &quot;Airport of Pristina - new center of the maltreatments
of Albanians&quot;. In the heading &quot;Opinions&quot;, the paper runs the article
&quot;Albanians with one or two visions&quot;. &quot;Confusion among the socialists of the
capital&quot; reports Dita Informacion, regarding the SP meeting of Tirana. The
paper publishes an interview with the executive director of the Non-
government Organizations Forum, Artan Spahiu under the title &quot;Which is the
position of the non-government organizations with the government&quot;.
<P>Under the title &quot;Stop smuggling&quot;, Koha Jone reports that the customs
officials of Gjirokastra, Kapshtica, Durresi etc, are suspended from work
and will be under penal prosecution. &quot;Flux of emigrants for Christmas&quot;,
reports the paper.
<P>&quot;Only the cursed writer belongs to all the times&quot;, reports Bashkimi in
the heading &quot;The tribune of intellectuals&quot;. &quot;Tirana SP divided: Should the
presidency resign or no?&quot;, reports Gazeta Shqiptare. &quot;Mejdani has called on
strengthening the unity within socialists&quot;, underlines the paper. Under the
title &quot;That is what Gramoz Ruci did on April 2&quot;, the paper cites the
chairman of the Parliamentary Commission on Defence, Order and National
Information Service (NIS), Azem Hjdari, who confirms the accuses against
Ruci, regarding the April 2 massacre. /kled/mt/k
<P><H5>Albanian Telegraphic Agency</H5>
<H3><A NAME="06">[06]</A> ALBANIAN WEIGHT-LIFTING FEDERATION ASKS MONEY FOR FIVE WEIGHT-LIFTERS
SOLD IN GREECE</H3>
TIRANA, DEC 21 (ATA) - Greek Weight-lifting Federation owes $90 000 to the
Albanian federation of Weight-lifting as a result of not paying the money
of buying our five talented weight-lifters, who contest for Greece,
confessed the Albanian Wight-lifting Federation.
<P>&quot;We do not exagerate in raising the voice when they are considered
Greek sport men&quot;, told ATA the Secretary General, Ferit Berberi on
Friday.
<P>Many Albanian weight-lifters take part in teams of other countries,
although they have achieved the highest point of their success here in
Albania, like Pirro Dhima (flagholder of the Greek team in the U.S.
Olympiade), Luan Shabani and many others.
<P>Apart from the movements of the last years, which led to the fall of
mant sport men in Albania, the weight-lifting moved forward to the course
of successes, all this thanks to the specification it has, but also to the
abilities and work done with these talented sport men. /e.gjyz/kei/mt/k
<P><H5>Albanian Telegraphic Agency</H5>
<H3><A NAME="07">[07]</A> THREE NEW DEPUTIES OF DEMOCRATIC PARTY SWORN IN</H3>
TIRANA, DEC 21 (ATA)- By A. Frasheri, Three new deputies of the
democratic Party were sworn in on Saturday.
<P>Base on law 7556, dated February 4,1992, changed by law 8055, dated
February 1, 1996 on &quot;The elections in the People's Assembly&quot;, Pandeli Pasko,
currently Albania's ambassador to Italy, Visar Zhiti, Counsellor at this
embassy, and Genc Juka, director of the Rural Development project, the
three deputies of the Democratic Party, asked to leave the deputy mandate
because their state tasks run counter to this mandate.
<P>At the meeting of December 19, 1996, the Commission of Mandate,
Immunity and Regulation of the People's Assembly proposed the replacement
of these three deputies by Mitro Cela, Orion Rusi and Burhan Kaceli,
according to order of the multi-nominal list of the Democratic Party,
deposited at the Central Electoral Commission.
<P>Mitro Cela has also been deputy of the Democratic Party in the past two
years, while Rusi and Kaceli are joinining parliament for the first time.
kei/lm/Z/
<P><H5>Albanian Telegraphic Agency</H5>
<H3><A NAME="08">[08]</A> TIRANA SP MEETING INTERRUPTED WITHOUT RESULT</H3>
TIRANA, DEC 21 (ATA)- By A. Baci,
<P>The request for an emergency conference of the Socialist Party and the
resignation of its presidency has been suspended because of an equal voting
in yesterday's meeting of the Tirana Steering Committee.
<P>The Tirana Steering Committee, split into two different clans, has
failed to provide a solution to the final draft of the report to be handed
over to the SP presidency.
<P>&quot;Because of the party's great problems, which are not being resolved,
the resignation of the presidency and the holding of an emergency
conference of the SP has been requested,&quot; the member of the steering
committee and presidency of the Tirana branch, Spartak Baci, told
ATA.
<P>&quot;Besides the request for a new vote of confidence for the presidency
and the emergency conference, there were also other problems which can be
widely discussed at an expanded meeting of the General Steering Committee
of the SP,&quot; said another member of the Tirana branch council, Lush Perpali.
jz/lm/Z/
<P><H5>Albanian Telegraphic Agency</H5>
<H3><A NAME="09">[09]</A> SEMINAR HELD WITH ALBANIAN MILITARY ATTACHES ABROAD AND ALBANIAN
REPRESENTATIVES TO NATO</H3>
TIRANA, DEC 21 (ATA)- The topic of the seminar with Albanian military
attaches abroad and Albanian military representatives to NATO, held over
the last four days in Tirana was: &quot;The Albanian renovated army has attained
substantial results in all fields of defence&quot;.
<P>The Defence Ministry spokesman says in this regard that an indication
of these results are the relations and broad cooperation of the Albanian
army with those of various countries, NATO members and partners.
<P>The realisation of several bilateral and multilateral exercises
including &quot;Peaceful eagle '96&quot; has testified to these relations and
cooperation. Of interest was the joint Albanian-German exercise &quot;Mati '96&quot;
and others. The peacekeeping company has been created and our troops joined
the IFOR and in the future they will join the SFOR,&quot; the spokesman
says.
<P>The seminar stressed that under the democratic governing Albania's
active role for interaction into the Eur.-Atlantic Security structures has
been intensified.
<P>The secretary of State for Defence, Leonard Demi, deputy Minister
Moisiu and other officials of the Defence Ministry read topics making
evident the serious performance of the Albanian army for interaction and
for reaching European standards. They also stressed Albania's determination
for NATO membership.
<P>The seminar also tackled professional issues and reports were read on
the Albanian army in the vision of the years 2000./JZ/LM/Z/
<P><H5>Albanian Telegraphic Agency</H5>
<H3><A NAME="10">[10]</A> CHRISTIAN-DEMOCRATS WANT PARTICIPATION IN DRAFTING CONSTITUTION</H3>
TIRANA, DEC 21 (ATA)-By A. Baci,
<P>The Presidency of the Christian-Democratic Party (CDP) and representatives
of this party in the local government discussed at a meeting Saturday the
request for participation in the parliamentary commission to engage in
drafting the constitution and for participation in the government, the
spokesman of this party, Fran Bruka, reports.
<P>The CDP, being a party of government coalition, has furthered its
demand for a greater participation in the government.
<P>&quot;The Christian-Democrats ask the cabinet of the construction minister
to complete the coalition framework with the DP&quot;, the participants in the
meeting said.
<P>The meeting also discussed finding concrete ways for supporting the two
communes in which the Christian-Democrats have won. jz/lm/Z/
<P><H5>Albanian Telegraphic Agency</H5>
<H3><A NAME="11">[11]</A> SUCCESSFUL OPERATIONS OF POLICE FORCES IN BAJRAM CURRI</H3>
TIRANA, DEC 21 (ATA)- The police forces in Bajram Curri, northern Albania,
have carried out a series of successful operations, which have resulted in
the arrest of several very wanted persons, authors of grave crimes,
according to the Interior Ministry spokesman.
<P>Mustafa Dollapi, accused of killing a citizen, and Ylber Gjonpalaj,
accused of killing a citizen and wounding another are now under arrest.
<P>Gezim Demiri, charged with wounding, has also been arrested.
<P>Also arrested are two other persons accused of robbing a citizen of his
property and of violent theft of the property of another citizen.
s.sh/jz/lm
<P><H5>Albanian Telegraphic Agency</H5>
<H3><A NAME="12">[12]</A> PARLIAMENT EXAMINES LAWS AND ADOPTS DECREES</H3>
TIRANA, DEC 21 (ATA)-By A. Baci,
<P>Albanian parliament on Saturday continued proceedings to examine a
series of laws and adopt several decrees.
<P>The draft-law on &quot;The further privatization of banks of commerce with
state capital&quot; was approved. Whereas the draft-law on a change to the law
on &quot;The areas of priority in tourism&quot; was put off for January.
<P>The draft-law on standardisation, after remarks by the parliamentary
commissions was referred back to the government for reexamination.
<P>The draft-law on &quot;Ratifying the loan agreement between the Islamic Bank
of Development and the Government of the Republic of Albania, on the
project to supply villages with drinking water&quot;, was approved.
<P>The draft-law on &quot;The ratification of the financial contract between
the Republic of Albania and the European Bank of Investment for the project
of the Vlora 220 KV substation of the Vlora-Fier line,&quot; was not approved.
<P>Finally, the draft-law on &quot;Some changes to the budget 1996&quot;, was
approved with the change made by the economic committee to article 4, an
article which had to do with the increase of funds for the customs
department.
<P>&quot;The government should explain to the parliament the reasons of the
deficit&quot;, the RP chairman, deputy Sabri Godo, said. jz/lm
