  <LI><A HREF="#11">[11]</A> LAW FOR PROTECTION AND IMPROVEMENT OF LIVING ENVIRONMENT ADOPTED
  <LI><A HREF="#12">[12]</A> GERMAN GOVERNMENT SUPPORT FOR PROTECTION OF OHRID AND PRESPA LAKES
  <LI><A HREF="#13">[13]</A> VANDALISM ON SEVERAL CHURCHES IN GOSTIVAR SURROUNDINGS
</DIR>
</H4>
<HR>
<H4>MILS NEWS</H4>
<H4>Skopje, 18 December, 1996</H4>
<H3><A NAME="01">[01]</A> GREEK-MACEDONIAN NEGOTIATIONS POSTPONED</H3>
Macedonian and Greek ambassadors Ivan Toshevski and Hristos Zaharakis
yesterday did not have the appointed meeting in New York and the media
report that the date for a new round of talks will additionally be
established.
<P>According to A-1 TV the spokesman of the mediator in the talks Saurus Vens
stated that the mediator will propose change in the reference with which
Macedonia is addressed in the UN of which there have been speculations in
the media these days.
<P>The Greek media have not reported the postponed round of Greek-Macedonian
talks as they usually do, reports the `Makfaks' agency explaining this with
the wave of strikes in Greece. However the reason for the Greek media's
silence might also be the possible movement upon the question about the
name differences. At such a comment pointed the article published in the
conservative Athens paper `Katimerini' where the name dispute is assessed
as a mistake of the foreign politics which has condemned Greece
to senseless exhaustion due to `a proportional second degree issue'.
According to `Katimerini the solution may already have been found and it
cites that it will most probably be one official name for all international
uses and that only Greece will call Macedonia by a name
dictated to them by their patriotism. Maybe the solution is at hand but now
there is search for a formula to decrease the politic price of accepting
the resolution which was announced since the beginning of the dispute,
concludes `Katimerini'.
<P>Regarding the Greek-Macedonian relations the Macedonia media yesterday
pointed out the letter from the Greek Culture Minister Evangelos Venizelos
who sent an invitation to his Macedonian colleague Minister Slobodan
Unkovski to participate in the solemn inauguration of Thessaloniki as the
European capital of culture in the following 1997. The invitation sent
through the Macedonian Liaison Department in Athens cites that the
manifestation will be of a Balkans dimension with a possible meeting of the
Culture ministers of the Balkans states which will deal with establishing a
Balkans culture net. The Greek Minister Venizelos cited in the invitation
that in the context of the Temporary Resolution in New York the
participation of Macedonia is of great significance both on bilateral and
Balkans level.
<H3><A NAME="02">[02]</A> MACEDONIAN-ALBANIAN DIALOGUE IN OSCE ORGANIZATION COMMENCED</H3>
In the `Kontinental' Hotel in Skopje yesterday commenced the two-day round
table on the subject `Building up harmonious inter-ethnic relations in
Macedonia' the initiator of which is the OSCE commissary for minorities
issues Maks Van Der Schtul. The media report that the suggestion for this
round table give by MR. Schtul was accepted by the Macedonian Government
while the Foreign Affairs Ministry appears as co-organiser. The two-day
Macedonian-Albanian dialogue is closed to the public and is divided in
three sessions in which introductory speakers will be one Macedonian and
one Albanian. The final word at the round table should be given by the
commissary Maks Van Der Schtul. Among the participants in the discussion
are the ministers Ljubomir Frchkovski, Vlado Popovski, Sofia Todorova,
Naser Ziberi and the leaders of the Liberal party Stojan Andov and the PDP
Abdurahman Aliti.
<H3><A NAME="03">[03]</A> ETHNOLOGY ASSOCIATION AT THE OSCE ROUND TABLE</H3>
Regarding the round table meeting on the subject `Building up harmonious
inter-ethnic relation in Macedonia' yesterday there was a reaction on the
part of the Ethnology Association which expressed protest assessing
that the round table has been organized incognito. `The round table has
been organized under a great pressure and demand on part of the political
parties of Albanian nationality in Macedonia and Albania directly which
openly stands in service of the Great-Albanian secessionism. The
paper `Fljaka e Vlazerimit' reports that in this unusual closed meeting
participate chosen Macedonian and Albanians and the itinerary covers issues
from the field of Albanian education and the usage of the Albanian language
in public life in the country an other serious inter-ethnic issues.
<P>We regret that not even one representative form the Macedonian ethnologist
was invited yet the ethno-political relations in our country will be
discussed dictated by the Albanian political subject.'
<P>The protest by the EAM Presidency further cites that with the issues
discussed behind closed doors the European political representatives
consciously or unconsciously impose partnership on Macedonia which carries
a fatal out- come
for the Macedonian ethnic region in all living areas in the country with
great consequences for the peace in the Balkans and wider.
<H3><A NAME="04">[04]</A> SOFIA `STANDARD' - MACEDONIA IN WAR WINDSTORM</H3>
After the statement given by the former State Secretary Henry Kissinger
that Macedonia is endangered by war the Sofia `Standard' reports
estimations from foreign diplomats that the situation in Macedonia is quite
intense and the US predict a new Balkans war. `Makpres' reports,
in the text titled as 'The Albanians in Macedonia create their own state
Ilirida' calling upon anonymous politicologists `Standard' emphasizes that
the real factor for a conflict in the Balkans are the Albanians in
Macedonia and Kosovo. The Albanian population in west Macedonia is very
separatist, claims the paper and adds: `They want to separate and join
Albania or Kosovo. The Albanian leader do not hide their wishes to create
their own federation in Macedonia in which they will get
autonomy leading towards creating a state `Ilirida'.  Citing this
`Standard' assesses that in that case the remaining part of Macedonia will
most probably gravitate towards Serbia not towards Bulgaria.
<P>`Standard', according to Makpres agency, in the same issue published the
statement of Marija Chavdarova - expert in the Bulgarian Defense Ministry -
who points out that the idea of a 6th war in the Balkans in the 20th
century had been begotten in the summer of 93 in the Institute for National
Strategic Researches by the University for National Defense of the US. She
also pointed out that the US have been dealing with the Balkans
war conflicts since 1992 .
<P>The complete war screenplay has bee published by Jeffrey Simon - expert and
researcher - in the material `Prevention of a 6th war in the Balkans in the
20th century', reports the Sofia paper. According to Simon the
current panicking situation in Serbia should light the fuse in Kosovo and
Macedonia. `Standard' calling upon anonymous diplomatic sources claims that
the Balkans politicians have been exploring the division of Macedonia
since 1993.
<H3><A NAME="05">[05]</A> ACCREDITATION OF ISRAELI AMBASSADOR IN MACEDONIA</H3>
Macedonian Chief of State Kiro Gligorov yesterday received Israeli
Ambassador Ran Kuriel in Macedonia and also handed him the accreditation
letters. The Macedonian president in the welcoming speech emphasized that
the appointing of the first Israeli ambassador in Macedonia presents a
continuity of the historically confirmed traditional friendly relations
between the Macedonian and Jewish people as well as of the successful
development of the relations between the two countries. Presenting the
Israeli President's regards the Israeli ambassador expressed the
willingness of the Israeli Government to continue the development of the
relations between the countries in all areas.
<P>The newly appointed Israeli ambassador in Macedonia Ran Kuriel yesterday
was received by the vice-president of the Macedonian Parliament, Tito
Petkovski, the Premier Branko Crvenkovski and Foreign Affairs Minister
Ljubomir Frchkovski.
<H3><A NAME="06">[06]</A> COMPENSATION FROM IRAQI-KUWAIT WAR FOR MACEDONIAN FIRMS NEXT YEAR</H3>
Macedonian Government Vice-president Ljube Trpevski yesterday in Geneva
had e meeting with Executive Secretary of the Compensation Commission by
the Security Council Carlos Alzamora and they discussed the Macedonian
demand for priority in solving the compensation from the Iraqi-Kuwait war
for the Macedonian firms. The Macedonian Television reports,
Almazora stated that he expects the problem to be solved in the course of
next year emphasizing that he will do everything possible in the direction
of a positive resolution. Official attitude of the Compensation
Commission by the UN Security Council , as it was stated by Alzamora, is
the following: the international community and the UN have the obligation
to help in the reestablishing the order which had been broken and to
compensate the justified demands of the firms and the damaged workers.
<P>Regarding the construction company `Pelagonija' from Skopje ( which has the
largest demand of compensation) Carlos Alzamora expressed expectation to
see this company again in the international waters of construction building
where it has always held an excellent and high reputation.
<H3><A NAME="07">[07]</A> THE CONSTRUCTION BUILDER'S STRIKE APPROACHING CULMINATION</H3>
The construction workers of `Mavrovo' have been on strike 10 days already
demanding payment of their salaries, and starting from yesterday there are
500 construction workers from `Pelagonija' on strike as well, report the
media.
<P>More than a thousand revolted construction workers yesterday blocked the
entrance to the Urban Planning Ministry where a meeting was to be held
between minister Jorgo Shundovski and the managers of the company with the
striking Committee of the independent syndicate `Mavrovo'. However the
representatives of the independent syndicate did not agree with the
attitude of Shundovski to include the `state syndicate' in the negotiations
and they left the session.
<P>`Dnevnik' reports, since yesterday the building of the railway towards
Bulgaria has been stopped and the workers joined the strikers in Skopje.
According to the Vise- President of the Independent Syndicate Union Blazze
Stojanovski the events will reach culmination in the following 2-3 days
with a large protest in front of the Government.
<H3><A NAME="08">[08]</A> MINISTER ZIBERI - NO CHANGES IN THE PENSIONING CONDITIONS</H3>
Regarding the speculations that are circling in the public these days about
the alleged restrictive measures in the Law for pension and invalid
insurance the Macedonian Television yesterday asked for a statement from
Labor and Social Policy Minister Naser Ziberi. According to Ziberi a
false panic is created among the citizens about the alleged reduced rights
for pensioning i.e. that there will be
a reduction of the pension base or that the age limits for both men and
women will be equal.
<P>Minister Ziberi gave the information that the law base for pensions will
continue to be 80% from the average salary, but it will also be related to
the average salary in the non-economy businesses. There will be no changes
regarding equalizing the male and female age limits. The changes in
the law regard procuring funds for timely payment of the pensions and
overcoming the finance deficit in the Pension and Invalid Insurance Fund,
stated Minister Ziberi.
<H3><A NAME="09">[09]</A> MORE CHANGES IN TAX SPHERE</H3>
A-1 TV reports, the Macedonian Government at the session held the day
before yesterday established a package of changes referring to the tax
sphere. With them the rate of taxation on the income is being reduced from
30% to 15%, and the income which will be used for investing will
be totally tax free. With the new changes the double taxation of the
dividend will be avoided and the prior 4 rates of sales tax and services
tax will be replaced with one rate of 13%. In the future coffee and alcohol
taxes will have to be paid it the total sum and taxpayer will
be the importer while demands for changes in the tobacco taxes are waiting
for better times. With the new tax changes taxation of the demand interest
rates will be avoided and in the rest only the real interest rates will
be taxed.
<H3><A NAME="10">[10]</A> `PALER MACEDONIAN' DEMANDS JUSTICE THROUGH COURT</H3>
As the owner of the air-transport company `Paler Macedonian' Vanja
Bitoljanu has informed yesterday this company has pressed charges against
the Traffic and Connection Minister Dimitar Buzlevski for abusing his
official position and authorization. Charges are pressed against Goran
Pavlovski - Manager of the Head Office for Civil Air Transport, Aleksandar
Chepeljugin - Manager of the Public Firm for Airport Services `Makedonija-
Skopje' and Ilija Iloski - President of the Administrative
Committee of the Public Firm all for abuse of their official duties and
authorities and for creating monopoly positions and causing disturbance on
the market.
<P>According to Bituljanu the charges have been pressed due to the fact that
the accuser (`Paler Macedonian') wants to give a modest contribution to the
respecting of the laws in the state i.e. to the direction of commencing the
functioning of the `worn-out phrase law state'.
<P>`Paler Macedonian' has been grounded for a long time now due to unpaid
demands towards the Public Firm for Airport Services `Makedonija-Skopje'.
The workers are being taken by the air company `MAT' and the airplanes are
returned to the renter. Vanja Bituljanu - owner of `Paler
Macedonian' has pointed out for many times now that his company is unjustly
grounded and that the rivals `MAT' and `Avioimpeks' are being unjustly
favored by the authorities.
<H3><A NAME="11">[11]</A> LAW FOR PROTECTION AND IMPROVEMENT OF LIVING ENVIRONMENT ADOPTED</H3>
The Macedonian Assembly at yesterday's 55th session has drafted the Law for
protection and improvement of the living environment. According to Minister
Jorgo Shundovski, this small `eco - constitution' is the first
Law of this kind in the country and it regulates the rights and duties in
the protection and improvement of the environment. The law predicts
establishing: an information system for monitoring the quality of the
living environment, inspectorate and Institute for Environment
Protection and providing means for inciting preventive measures
for protection and a special fund for environment improvement will be
established.
<P>During the session in the Macedonian General Assembly in front of the
Assembly building there was a rally of the ecologists for support of the
Law. About 300 ecologists wanted to pressure the members of the Parliament
to draft the Law which is the fundamental prerequisite for
improving the living environment. in Macedonia.
<P>The Parliament members at yesterday's session drafted the Law for tobacco
but they did not succeed in drafting the La w for legal procedure due to
lack of quorum. In the amendment dispute for this law the demands of the
PDP Party were not accepted - they demanded the lawsuit
procedure to be carried out in the language of the nationalities unless the
client has command of the Macedonian language.
<H3><A NAME="12">[12]</A> GERMAN GOVERNMENT SUPPORT FOR PROTECTION OF OHRID AND PRESPA LAKES</H3>
The German Government, through its Agency for Technical Cooperation,
approved 600.000 DM. for commencing the project of economic development and
protection of the environment in the coastal area of the Ohrid and Prespa
Lakes, reported Radio Tirana yesterday. The funds for this project should
be approved by the European Organization for Protection of the Human
Environment and some other organizations, reports `Makpres'. This help
will also include Macedonia and Greece with the aim to gather the
citizens to work together on the economic development in these regions and
on the protection of the lakes regardless of their nationality.
<H3><A NAME="13">[13]</A> VANDALISM ON SEVERAL CHURCHES IN GOSTIVAR SURROUNDINGS</H3>
In the Gostivar village Vrapchishte a few days ago unknown doers entered
three churches and damaged them, reports `Vecher' From the church Sveti
Atanas the vandals stole money and some gifts - embroideries, and they lit
fire within the church `Sveti Ilija' thus destroying the
woodworks. The entrance doors of the churches were damaged by tools and
other objects.
<P><H4>(end)</H4>
<H4>mils news 18 December, 1996</H4>
