<TITLE>Antenna: News in English, 96-12-18</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<body bgcolor=#FFFFFF>
<center><a href="/info"><IMG SRC="/gifs/hrnet.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="[HR-Net Banner]"></a><BR></center>

<H2>Antenna: News in English, 96-12-18</H2>
<H5><A HREF="/news/greek/ant1en">Antenna Radio News in English</A> Directory - <A HREF="96-12-17.ant1en.html">Previous Article</A> - <A HREF="96-12-19.ant1en.html">Next Article</A></H5>
<H4>From: Antenna Radio &lt;<A HREF="http://www.antenna.gr">http://www.antenna.gr</A>&gt; - email: <A HREF="mailto:antenna@antenna.ath.forthnet.gr">antenna@antenna.ath.forthnet.gr</A></H4>
<H3>News in English, of 13/12/1996</H3>
<HR>
<H3>TITLES</H3>
<H4>
<UL>
<LI>President Clinton's commitment to resolving Greek- Turkish differences
and the Cyprus issue***.
<LI>How popular are the parties? All the numbers from the first poll since
the election***.
<LI>And, Antenna and its viewers put books into the hands of children***.
</UL>
</H4>
<HR>
<H4> CLINTON</H4>
US president Bill Clinton says he is determined to help resolve Greek-
Turkish differences and the Cyprus issue during his second term.
<H4> SPIRIDAKI</H4>
The farmers' protests, now in their third week, have attracted the
attention of the media around the world.
<P>CNN asked Antenna's New York correspondent, Alexandra Spiridaki, about the
farmers' and the government's tough economic policies.
<H4> MRB POLL</H4>
The first major poll on voter preferences carried out since the national
elections in September show that the two main parties are in a slump.
<P>The MRB survey shows that Pasok and New Democracy are pretty much where
they are when they last major survey was carried out BEFORE the election.
<H4>SKLIVA-STEPHANOPOULOS</H4>
The new Miss World, Irini Skliva, is back in Greece for the holidays,
before she begins her rigorous one-year reign as the world's most beautiful
woman. Her itinerary will be packed with a number of appearances at events
in aid of children with special needs.
<P>And, as she prepares to dive into her assignments, Irini got some sage
advice from the president of Greece.
<H4>ANT1 BOOK DRIVE</H4>
Antenna television recently said a big &quot;thanks&quot; to its viewers for their
show of Christmas generosity.
<P>Antenna sponsored a book drive to get books to children in remote parts of
Greece, but also to Greek kids living abroad.
<H4>ND REVIEW</H4>
Kostas Simitis's ability to take command of Pasok and lead Pasok to a
general election victory left some of New Democracy's top members
determined to oust party leader Miltiades Evert.
<H4>VOLUNTEERS</H4>
It's Christmas time and offering comes a lot in our mind, especially in
those holy days of love.
<P>Antenna's Maria Papapanagiotou went to a shelter for elderly people, where
volunteers work to take care of people in need.
<H4>&copy; ANT1-Radio 1996</H4>
<HR>
<H5><A HREF="/news/greek/ant1en">Antenna Radio News in English</A> Directory - <A HREF="96-12-17.ant1en.html">Previous Article</A> - <A HREF="96-12-19.ant1en.html">Next Article</A></H5>
