<HEAD>
<TITLE>RADOR: News from Romania, 96-12-17</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<body bgcolor=#FFFFFF>
<center><a href="/info"><IMG SRC="/gifs/hrnet.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="[HR-Net Banner]"></a><BR></center>

<H2>RADOR: News from Romania, 96-12-17</H2>
<H5><A HREF="/news/balkans/rador">The Press Agency of the Romanian Radio (RADOR Society)</A> Directory - <A HREF="96-12-16.rador.html">Previous Article</A> - <A HREF="96-12-18.rador.html">Next Article</A></H5>
<H4>From: RADOR Press Agency &lt;<A HREF="http://indis.ici.ro/romania/news/rador.html">http://indis.ici.ro/romania/news/rador.html</A>&gt;</H4>
<H4>DECEMBER 17th, 1996</H4>
<HR>
<H3>CONTENTS</H3>
<H4>
<DIR>
  <LI><A HREF="#01">[01]</A> Mourning day in Timisoara
  <LI><A HREF="#02">[02]</A> Assistance from the International Monetary Fund
  <LI><A HREF="#03">[03]</A> Donation of books for Moldova
  <LI><A HREF="#04">[04]</A> Weather
  <LI><A HREF="#05">[05]</A> Currency rates
</DIR>
</H4>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="01">[01]</A> Mourning day in Timisoara</H3>
Timisoara, a town in Western Romania, declared Tuesday a mourning day to
celebrate its heroes. A rally was held yesterday in this town, where the
December 1989 Revolution started. On the occasion Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu promised the much-sought-after truth about the events that
took place in Timisoara and the rest of Romania seven years ago. Also
addressing the rally were Iurie Rosca, chairman of the Christian Democratic
Front of the Republic of Moldova, various representatives of the parties in
the new government coalition and participants in the 1989 revolution. The
speakers underscored Timisoara's role in that revolution and in keeping up
civic awareness in the country in the years that followed 1989.<EM>RRI- RADOR,
December 17th, 1996</EM>
<H3><A NAME="02">[02]</A> Assistance from the International Monetary Fund</H3>
In its first official meeting the new Romanian government hailed the
assistance extended by the International Monetary Fund in designing its
economic programme. A new round of negociations will be held in mid-January
in Bucharest between IMF representatives and the National Bank of Romania,
to redicuss a stand-by agreement for Romania. The Romanian government has
announced it would guarantee a 200 million dollars foreign credit to
finance oil imports and has resolved to grant a 120 thousand dollar
assistance to help people of Iassy county, eastern Romania, cope with the
effects of massive landslides.<EM>RRI-RADOR, December 17th,1996</EM>
<H3><A NAME="03">[03]</A> Donation of books for Moldova</H3>
The Romanian government has given a donation of books for 3,000 public
libraries in Moldova. The total amount is 60.000 books, worth 300 million
lei. The donation comes to complete a precedent donation of 112,000 books.
The books will be given to the libraries that have little works in Latin
writing.<EM>RRA-RADOR, December 17th, 1996</EM>
<H3><A NAME="04">[04]</A> Weather</H3>
Weather in Romania is nice but cold. Highest temperatures will range from -
2to 6 degrees Celsius. This morning, the reeding in Bucharest was 1 degree
Celsius.<EM>RRA-RADOR, December 17th, 1996 </EM>
<H3><A NAME="05">[05]</A> Currency rates</H3>
The exchange rates of the national currency, the leu, valid for today, and
set by the National Bank of Romania, are: 1 USD = 3,769 lei;lei; 1 CHF = 2,
883 lei; 1 FRF = 725 lei; 1 GBP = 6,266 lei.<EM>RRA-RADOR, December 17th,
1996</EM>
<HR>
